title: tasty nut granola
directions: Combine ingredients (except raisins) in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan; mix well.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 250°.
Stir occasionally. Remove from oven.
Stir in raisins.
Cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 6 cups.

title: graham delights
directions: Boil margarine, butter and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Line a large flat pan with aluminum foil, dull side up.
Lay crackers on foil and pour syrup over.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: hot tamale dip
directions: Saute onion, then add the other ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts.
Serve with Fritos.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Bake in a large sheet cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Cool.

title: one bowl macaroons
directions: Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets immediately.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: clear tomato soup
directions: Saute celery, carrots and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients except consomme.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour; strain.
Add hot consomme; reheat.
Serve hot.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Saute diced onion and pepper in margarine.
Cook 8 to 12 potatoes.
Cool and dice.
Dice 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese.

title: margaret's fresh peach pie
directions: Blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold in peach slices.
Put mixture into pie crust and chill for several hours.

title: peel a pound soup
directions: Put in a big pot of water and cook until tender.
Add salt and Parmesan cheese to servings.

title: pie cobbler
directions: Melt the margarine in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle sugar over the peaches.
Mix the milk and 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour over the fruit, but don't mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add remaining ingredients, except onions.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Dip onion rings into batter.
Fry in deep cooking oil (375°) until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together mayonnaise and soup.
In glass 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer broccoli, cream mixture, cheese slices (to cover) and cracker crumbs; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Add egg and molasses and beat until well blended.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together and add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill dough. Then shape dough in balls.
Roll in white sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
These cookies get softer in a day or so if covered tightly.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups of liquid.
Heat juice and add to jello.
Chill; fold in cottage cheese, pineapple and mayonnaise.
Put in mold and congeal.

title: asian slaw
directions: Combine first four ingredients, set aside.
Remove flavor packets from noodles, and crush noodles; set this aside, also. Whisk together contents from flavor packets, sugar, vinegar, and oil.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
When ready to serve, combine noodles with slaw mixture.
Pour oil mixture over this and toss well.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon and bacon grease; cook for 10 minutes.
Add bacon and bacon grease.

title: dump cake
directions: "Dump" into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan the cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple, cake mix, coconut and nuts.
Drizzle melted margarine over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, cook ham with salad oil until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add onion, celery and carrot; cook until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vegetable soup, water, beans with their liquid, oregano, bay leaf and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in pasta; cook about 12 minutes more, or until pasta is tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve.

title: cooked potato salad dressing
directions: In double boiler, combine salt, mustard, sugar, pepper and flour.
Stir in slowly a mixture of egg yolks, butter, milk and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Mix with cooked red potatoes and celery.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dressing.

title: quick pasta salad
directions: Mix dressing and Salad Supreme.
Add pasta and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: hot ham dip
directions: Mix all together, except nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. (Bake in the same dish as you will serve in.) Sprinkle nuts on top.
Serve hot with Wheat Thins or other crackers.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all the liquids together and add 1/3 to the rice in a casserole dish or pan.
Lay parts of chickens on top.
Pour remaining liquids over all.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and slivered almonds.
Bake, uncovered, 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: market salad
directions: In large bowl whisk together first five ingredients.
Add vegetables; toss thoroughly to blend.
Add cheese; toss lightly. Cover and chill two to three hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chunky dressing
directions: Combine chopped cucumber, green pepper, radish, green onion and pimiento.
Stir in dairy sour cream, mayonnaise or salad dressing, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: broiled chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in a broiling pan, skin side down.
Rub and squeeze 1/2 of lemon.
Brush with 1/2 of melted butter.
Blend salt, pepper and paprika and sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over chicken. Then sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.

title: cheesy broiled ham slice
directions: Cook frozen baby lima beans as directed; drain.
Diagonally slice outer edge of fat on ham slice at 1 inch intervals to prevent curling.
Place ham on rack in broiler pan.

title: chicken with sweet peas
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Drop chicken pieces into bag and shake to coat each piece.
Melt butter and heat oil in a skillet.
Fry coated chicken in butter-oil mixture until golden brown.
Add carrots, bay leaf, oregano and leeks. Add chicken broth and cook until chicken is almost tender.
Add potatoes and peas and continue to cook until chicken, potatoes and peas are tender.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour cucumber pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into 1-inch pieces.
Soak in lime water to cover overnight.
Drain and soak in fresh water 4 hours, changing water every hour.
Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add pickles and bring to a boil again.
Make lime water by using 1 cup slacked lime in 1 gallon water.
Makes 8 pints.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Pour pumpkin mix into dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add part of flour and mix well.
Add chocolate syrup, mixing as you go.
Then add rest of flour; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Bakes well in a greased Pyrex dish. Dish size should be 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch.

title: divinity(makes 8 dozen pieces)
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in heavy saucepan over low heat. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Cook without stirring to 255°. Remove from heat and pour in a constant fine stream into already beaten egg whites. Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts. Spread into a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan and cut into squares when firm.

title: honey butter
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: squash fritters
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water in saucepan until tender; drain.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and parsley flakes; mix well.
Add egg, baking powder and sugar; mix well. Add enough flour to mixture to form stiff dough.
Roll 1 teaspoonful at a time in flour to coat.
Deep fry in hot oil until brown; drain.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: meat nachos
directions: Brown hamburger and pour into large crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir as cheese melts.
Serve with chips.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix soda with dates; pour the boiling water over and allow to stand until cool.
Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten egg, vanilla and salt.
Combine with the date mixture and stir in flour.
Add nuts and pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Test for doneness.

title: fried rice fiesta
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add rice and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until rice is brown.
Add water to broth to make 2 cups; add to rice.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add tomato or tomato soup; continue cooking until all liquid is absorbed.

title: easy rolls
directions: Combine in large bowl first 4 ingredients; stir until melted. Cool until lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast in water; let set 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir and add to cooled mixture.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Add 2 cups flour; beat well with a spoon.
Stir in rest of flour slowly.
Put in bowl and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: sourdough rolls
directions: In another dish, mix yeast with warm water (dissolve the yeast).
Then add to this yeast and water mixture the oil and buttermilk.
Now add the liquid mixture to the dry mixture and mix well.
Pinch off what you want to cook at the present time and roll it in flour. Grease muffin pan.
Pinch off for each roll and put in pan.
Butter tops of rolls with melted butter.
Cook at about 375° until done.
Place balance of mixture in an airtight covered container.
Place in refrigerator.
This mixture will keep for about a week.
Pinch off and cook as you wish.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Last, add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Mixture will be stiff, but juice from apples will make it juicy.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In mixing bowl beat the eggs.
Add oil and pumpkin.
Beat until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Gradually beat into pumpkin mixture.
Pour batter into 5 greased 5 x 2 1/2 x 2 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 50-55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Or can bake in 2 greased 8 x 4 x 23 inch pans for 75-80 minutes.

title: spinach dip bread bowl
directions: Thaw and thoroughly drain spinach.
Combine rest of ingredients except bread.
Chill 3 hours.
Hollow center of loaf and save the center and cut up for dipping.
Fill center of loaf with dip.
Surround with bread cubes and fresh vegetables.
Enjoy! Refrigerate leftovers.
tags: Mrs. Grass homestyle vegetable soup mix

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, nuts, margarine and 1/2 can of evaporated milk together until moist.
Pat 1/2 of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Melt caramels and remaining evaporated milk in saucepan.
Pour over the chocolate mixture.
Add remaining cake mixture by sprinkling over top.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate to cool and then cut into bars.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Add mayo last. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve!

title: blackberry cake
directions: Beat eggs, add oil and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for one hour or until done.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Drizzle blackberry pie filling over the top.

title: round steak supreme
directions: Sprinkle steak with tenderizer then pound steak.
Cut into serving pieces.
Salt and pepper, roll in flour and brown well on both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Place potatoes on top of meat. Dilute mushroom soup with water.
Add onion and pour over potatoes and meat.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
Prepare a tossed green salad and you have an easy and tasty meal.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, peppers and onions overnight with salt sprinkled over top.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients:
sugars, turmeric, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to rolling boil.
Can in sterilized jars.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar, water and butter. Pour over beets and simmer slowly for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in usual manner folding in raw apples and flour coated nuts last.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: corn meal taco shells
directions: Mix together with wire whisk until very few lumps remain. Pour 3 to 4 tablespoons of batter onto hot griddle and smooth out in a circular motion until thin.
Use more batter for larger shells.
Turn when edges dry and begin to lift off griddle.
Fill with choice of taco ingredients.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown the
ground
beef
and
drain grease.
Take the 3 cans and stir in with the ground beef until it boils.
Crumble up the tostado chips
in a rectangular casserole dish and pour the mix over the
chips. Sprinkle the shredded cheese over the sauce and put in the oven at 350° until the cheese melts, then it's ready to serve.

title: swiss steak
directions: Preheat broiler unit in range. Cut round steak along natural separations. Trim all visible fat and connective tissue. Cut into serving size pieces. Coat meat with a mixture of the flour, salt and pepper. Spray bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray. Place steak in pan. Position pan so top of meat is 4 or 5-inches from heating element. Brown steak, top side only, for 5 to 7 minutes. Check often after the first 5 minutes to see that it doesn't burn. Remove pan from oven. Set oven temperature to 350°. Add remaining ingredients to meat. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together in bowl peanut butter, cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and chill about 1 hour.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter Crisco until pea
size.
Stir in milk.
Drop by large tablespoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Gather tender young poke leaves early in the morning ,while the dew is still on, and gather a large shopping bag full.
Pick over and wash through 3 waters.
Place in a kettle with one or two cups of water, a piece of salt pork or bacon drippings.
Bring to a good boil and when poke wilts down into the water, reduce heat and cook slowly until tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Then add bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° in greased Bundt pan for about 45 minutes.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until very crisp and reserve drippings.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender and clear.
Remove from heat to cool slightly.
Mix together vinegar (add more or less for desired "German" flavor) with yellow mustard and add onions.
Stir constantly to prevent curdling.
Cool onions to warm, then add Miracle Whip.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Coat bottom of small casserole with one third of mixture and cover with a layer of sliced potatoes.
Add two more layers of mixture and potatoes for a total of three layers of each.
Top with cheddar cheese.
Crumble bacon over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: one gallon muffin mix
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy, then add sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Store at least one day in icebox or cool place before baking, then bake only the amount needed.
The remaining dough will keep for days or weeks.
Keep refrigerated.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: favorite barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; simmer for 10 minutes or until flavors are blended, stirring frequently.
Tomato sauce may be substituted for part of the catsup, if desired.

title: lisa's low-fat chocolate pound cake
directions: Grease pan or spray with Pam. Stir all ingredients together with mixer. Pour in pan and bake 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel-nut apples(caramel apples are rolled in crunchy walnuts)
directions: Advance preparation:
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, light corn syrup and butter or margarine.
Bring mixture to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until soft-ball stage (234° to 240° on candy thermometer).
Stir in vanilla; remove from heat. Insert a wooden stick into blossom end of each apple.
Dip apple in caramel mixture, turning until apple is completely coated. Immediately roll bottom half of coated apple in chopped walnuts. Repeat with remaining apples.
Place on baking sheet covered with waxed paper.
Chill until caramel is firm.
Makes 6.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Arrange apples in unbaked pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Cut in butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Cool.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine rice, ham, soup, mushrooms, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Place slices of pineapple, cut into halves and garnished with whole cloves over top of mixture.
Dot with butter and brown sugar; bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp or tuna dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in tomato soup.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to tomato soup mixture.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Allow to cool slightly and then add celery, peppers, onion, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Mix and add crumbled or diced shrimp or tuna and the Miracle Whip.
Put in mold and chill until firm.
Serve on plate with crackers.

title: melody's celery seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt and mustard with a little vinegar.
Beat well and add oil and remaining vinegar.
Beat celery seed in last.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onions, cracker crumbs, eggs, salt, milk and ginger. Shape mixture into meatballs and brown. Simmer until cooked through. Add pineapple chunks and reserve syrup. Mix cornstarch and sugar. Stir in pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth. Stir constantly over medium heat until thickened. Pour over meatballs and pineapple chunks; heat through.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onions, carrots and celery in bacon fat until transparent.
Combine rest of ingredients in kettle.
Let simmer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, almonds and sour cream together.
Put crackers on bottom, but save enough to put on top.
Melt margarine before putting cracker crumbs on bottom of dish, then put chicken on top of crackers.
Put other mixture on top followed by cracker crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Salt cooked squash.
Mix egg yolks, sour cream and flour. Fold in egg whites.
Layer half of the squash, egg mixture and cheese in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Crumble bacon; sprinkle on top.
Repeat layers.
Mix butter and crumbs; sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: calcannon
directions: Boil vegetables and mash together. Add butter.

title: beef and mushrooms
directions: In hot skillet, add 1/4 cup of hot cooking oil.
Brown onion, then add beef.
Cook until about half done.
Then add drained and cut mushrooms.
When they are hot and cooking again, add hot sauce and pepper.
Simmer until beef is done, then add soup and 1/4 cup of water.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
It must be stirred often. Serve on toast or noodles.

title: herbed cheese and sprout sandwiches
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature for about an hour to blend.
Spread mixture on half the slices.
Top each with sprouts and another slice of bread.
Serve as is or cut to desired size.

title: red dragon in-a-hurry-cake
directions: Cover the bottom of a Bundt pan with brown sugar, about 1/2 inch deep.
Evenly distribute cherries around the bottom of the pan; set aside.
Mix cake as per the instructions on the box. Pour batter into Bundt pan on top of cherries and brown sugar. Bake at 325° until done.
Allow cake to cool for at least 1/2 hour before turning cake onto a plate.
Makes a beautiful cherry upside-down cake.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar; cook 4 minutes on High in the microwave.
Stir in dry roasted peanuts and cook 3 minutes on High.
Remove from microwave and stir in margarine and vanilla flavoring; cook 1 minute.
Stir in soda.
Pour onto prepared surface and spread.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in sugars, egg, peanut butter, butter and shortening until smooth.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Cover; refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough by teaspoon into 2 1/2-inch fingers on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until light brown, about 8 minutes. Cool.
Coat one end of cookie with Cocoa Glaze.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: good beets
directions: Cook beets until tender and drain.
Mix sugar, water, vinegar and cornstarch together well in saucepan.
Add beets and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: crisp cucumber pickles
directions: Put all ingredients, except cucumbers, in jar with cover. Blend until sugar is dissolved. Add cucumbers. Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Place in 10 x 6 x 1-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese.
Add milk, mayonnaise and egg, stirring until blended.
Pour over broccoli. Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over soup mixture. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Shake chicken pieces in flour in a paper bag. Store overnight in refrigerator. Fry wings in 1-inch oil until lightly brown. Set aside to cool. Mix soy sauce, sugar, garlic, ginger, sesame oil, sesame seeds and onions. Dip wings in sauce and place in cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until heated through, approximately 20 to 30 minutes. Serve hot as appetizer. Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in frypan, breaking it up as it fries.
Add onion to pan and cook.
Add remaining ingredients.
Slowly bring to boil, then turn to simmer for about 2 hours.

title: nora faye's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside. Cut up margarine and pour boiling water over it. Stir until melted; cool. Add cold water. Stir in sugar, salt, slightly beaten egg and yeast mixture. Mix well. Add 2 cups flour and mix well. Add remaining 2 cups flour. Beat well. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: tuna-cheese buns
directions: Combine all ingredients except buns.
Spoon between buttered split buns.
Wrap each bun in aluminum foil.
Bake in foil in 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken fettucini alfredo
directions: Season chicken pieces with black pepper and garlic salt.
Cook in 1/2 stick of margarine over low heat until tender.
Dice the chicken.
Saute green onions (lightly) in pan chicken was cooked in.
Add to diced chicken.
Cook fettucini according to package directions, adding 1 tablespoon oil to water.
Drain noodles (do not rinse).
Return noodles to pan.
Add the 1 stick of margarine and canned milk.
Toss with forks until margarine is melted.
Toss in Parmesan cheese, chicken, onions and 1 tablespoon parsley flakes.
Serve immediately.

title: dollies' cranberry salad
directions: Mix together hot water, lemon Jell-O, juice of lemon and orange.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put ingredients into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
(I double the recipe in order to have a thicker gelatin salad.)
Good with poultry, served with chicken, duck or turkey.

title: hot clubhouse sandwiches(power level: low, 30% and high, 100%)
directions: Arrange the slices of toasted bread in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Layer turkey and ham on bread.
Place butter in a 1-quart casserole. Microwave on Low (30%) for 30 to 45 seconds or until softened.
Stir in soup and Worcestershire sauce until smooth. Pour over sandwiches.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Puree artichoke hearts.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with wheat crackers or bread sticks.

title: three bean bake
directions: Fry onion and bacon; pour off grease.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: autumn stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except beef in a large kettle. Brown ground beef and drain. Add to kettle and simmer.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce; set aside.
Slice rolls in half and place bottom half in baking dish.
Cover with sliced ham and cheese slice.
Place mayonnaise mixture on other half of rolls and place on top of ham and cheese.
Pour 3/4 stick of butter over the rolls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin angel squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts with pastry blender until crumbly. Press firmly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: martha washington fudge balls
directions: Mix together with hands thoroughly.
Make into small balls and refrigerate for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soups and onion soup mix together.
Spread across bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, pepper and paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt mamie's compressed fruit cake
directions: Grind raisins, dates, pineapple, and citron through chopper. Cut cherries in half and nuts in pieces.
Keep orange juice near at hand for working mixture like dough - dipping fingers in orange juice prevents the material from sticking to hands.

title: hawaiian rice and beans
directions: Prepare fresh coconut milk or use prepared shredded coconut dropped into boiling water.
Boil coconut-water mixture for 10 minutes.
Strain through a large fine mesh strainer.
Press to get out all the coconut milk.
Throw away coconut thrash.
Pour kidney beans into coconut juice and bring to a boil.
Add garlic clove, salt and green onions.
While boiling, pour in rice.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring once or twice until thoroughly cooked.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll steak in flour, brown in skillet on both sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add beef broth, mushrooms and sour cream. Simmer until sour cream is melted.
Serve over buttered egg noodles.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut in squares.
Bake this cake in a small square pan.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Add milk
to
softened	cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add
remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set in refrigerator until cool. Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add egg yolks.
Add strawberries.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 9 x 11-inch pan, greased and floured, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can use 3 cake pans.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix 100% bran and water and let stand for 1 minute.
Cream butter and sugar together and add to first mixture.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to wet mixture gradually.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: In saucepan, heat 2 cans crushed pineapple, sugar and flour to boiling.
Remove from heat and add cherries and dry jello.
Let cool.
Add walnuts and bananas.
Fill 2 pie shells.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato-cauliflower-tomato curry
directions: Heat up oil.
When hot, add caraway seed.
When seed makes a crackling noise, lower heat and add chopped onions, ginger and green chilies to it.
Saute over medium heat until onions become translucent.
Add salt, spices and chopped tomatoes; saute for a few more minutes.
Add potatoes and cauliflower; cook over medium heat, stirring from time to time.
Add a few tablespoons of water as needed to help the cooking.
When the potatoes and cauliflower become tender, add green peas to it.
Stir and cook a few more minutes.
When done, garnish with fresh cilantro.

title: salmon dip
directions: Discard bones and skin from can of salmon.
Cream together all ingredients with mixer.
Will be very thick.
Serve with crackers at room temperature.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, green pepper and mushrooms; drain.
Season. Add pizza sauce to beef and cooked macaroni.
Alternate layers of cheeses and pepperoni with meat mixture, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese food, softened cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine; mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Make into a ball.
Garnish with nuts, if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: sugar-free banana-date cookies
directions: Cream bananas, dates and oil together.
Add salt, oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Cook all ingredients in a large pot; cook until tomatoes have fallen apart and onions have become tender.
Stir in rice, then place in serving dish.
This side item is a great compliment to fried chicken, chops and grilled steak.
Meal should be served with biscuit and honey to round out the perfect Southern Charm.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: lamb meatballs with herb tomato sauce
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and 1 clove minced garlic.
Cook and stir over medium heat until onion is tender. Transfer to medium mixing bowl.
Add lamb, half and half, parsley, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 16 meatballs. Place in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until browned on all sides.
Remove meatballs and set aside.

title: zesty grilled pork medallions
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients; mix well. Set aside 1 cup for dipping; cover and refrigerate. Pour remaining marinade into a large resealable plastic bag; add the pork. Seal bag and turn to coat; refrigerate overnight. Drain and discard marinade. Grill pork, covered, over indirect medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes or until a meat thermometer reads 160°. Warm the dipping sauce; serve with sliced pork. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican hamburger cornbread
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix cornmeal, buttermilk, eggs, oil and creamed corn.
In a large skillet, spray the bottom or melt shortening.
Add 3/4 of cornmeal mix.
Top with hamburger, onions and hot pepper.
Top with Cheddar cheese; then pour remaining cornbread mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chocolate delight pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares of chocolate with 1/4 cup milk in large microwavable bowl at High, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Gently stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature until pie can be cut easily.
Melt remaining chocolate about 15 seconds.
Drizzle over pie.
(May need to add a few drops of milk to chocolate for drizzle.)

title: shish kabobs("souvlakia")
directions: Cut meat from boneless leg of lamb into small pieces, making about 18 pieces in all.
Combine the salt, pepper, oregano, garlic, onion, bay leaves, lemon juice and oil and pour over the lamb.
Mix well and allow to stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix all together, except Chinese noodles.
Cover with noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine flour and sugar.
Using a pastry blender or fork, cut margarine in until mixture resembles fine meal.
Press into greased pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Meanwhile, combine eggs, brown sugar and vanilla; beat well. Stir in baking soda, walnuts, raisins and coconut.
Spoon over hot crust.
Spread to cover evenly.
Return to oven; bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until top is set.
Cool completely. Cut into bars.

title: tuna and pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except rotini.
Cook rotini until firm.
Cool and add to mixture.
Cover; refrigerate overnight to improve flavors.

title: cool pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into an 11-inch graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: rush-hour simmer dinner
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, arrange the pasta, undrained chicken, frozen peas, carrots and sliced onion.
Add the chicken broth and sprinkle with tarragon.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until noodles are just tender. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving contains: 399 calories; 30 grams protein; 40 grams carbohydrates; 13 grams fat; 77 mg. cholesterol and 861 mg. sodium.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Sprinkle over Buckle.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°. Serve warm.
Some like a little milk with it.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: This is a family recipe from Bologna, Italy (my Gramma Zandi).

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients in cake pan (greased), in the order listed. Cut margarine in squares over top.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute celery, onions and bell pepper.
Layer ingredients in a large casserole.
Add 1 cup water.
Spoon celery soup over the top and bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In large pot, cover whole chickens with water.
Add carrots, onion and celery.
Bring to boil, then simmer for about 2 hours. Remove chicken and vegetables from pot.
Debone chicken and cut up.
Cut tortillas into quarters and layer on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Arrange a layer of chicken and vegetables, olives, chilies, onions and cheese.
Repeat a layer.
Mix soups and pour over top.
Let soak through.
Top with more cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Pound pork with the back of a cleaver (this is to tenderize the pork).
Then cut into one inch squares.
Marinate with above items for at least 20 minutes or more.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Chill and slice.

title: tomato relish
directions: Grind together tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Add 2 tablespoons pickling salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Add sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed.
Bring to a boil and boil 20 minutes.
Drain well again.
Cool completely.
Add mustard and mayonnaise.
Seal in jars.
Stores well in refrigerator. Excellent served with crackers.

title: snowy fudge
directions: Heat sugar and milk to 235°.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into tiny buttered muffin tins.

title: seafood quiche squares
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle partially baked crust with cheeses, shrimp and crabmeat. In large bowl, combine half and half, eggs, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Return to oven and bake an additional 25 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and edges are golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes. Cut into squares.
Serve warm.
Makes 60 appetizers.

title: peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Stir in lightly through peaches.
Heap in pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: saucy ham and potato bake
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, stirring until melted.
Toss potatoes in cheese sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole, reserving 1 cup potato slices.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Note:
Egg vinegar and cold water to equal 1 cup.

title: ken's holiday snack mix
directions: Put dry ingredients in large roasting pan with lid and stir. Mix salad oil, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and seasoned salt in bowl; stir together and drizzle over dry ingredients.
Put lid on roasting pan and gently shake to mix all ingredients.
Bake in very slow oven (250°) for 2 hours, gently stirring or shaking every 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 8-quarts.

title: croquettes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Shape into ovals about the size of large meatballs.
Pour can of tomato juice over croquettes. Cover with lid.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until juice cooks down to a thick sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn chip dip
directions: *How spicy you like it depends on using hot or mild.
I use 1 mild and 1 unflavored Velveeta.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies. Cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork. Sprinkle with coffee and set aside.

title: pink dessert
directions: Sprinkle box of Jell-O into Cool Whip, mixing well.
Add cottage cheese and mix until cottage cheese does not show white. Drain pineapple and cherries.
Add to Cool Whip and cottage cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows.
Stir well.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Serve.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Grease and flour two 10-inch tube pans. In a large mixing bowl, beat butter with sugar and cream until smooth. Add eggs and flour; mix just to combine. Slowly drizzle buttermilk and vanilla, 2 teaspoons at a time, until incorporated. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour until a toothpick inserted into the middle of each cake comes out clean.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Strain juice from pineapple and use when mixing Jell-O.
Add to Jell-O the cream cheese and marshmallows (add while Jell-O is hot). Beat with eggbeater to mix.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to set. Add nuts and pineapple.
Pour into mold.

title: o.j.'s biscuits
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour, oil and enough milk to make sticky batter.
Place extra flour on plate and flop batter on top.
Pat all sides with flour and cut into round biscuits with mouth of a glass.
Place into greased round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Makes 5 good size biscuits.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients sifted together.
Stir.
Add nuts and apples; stir.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to margarine mixture, mixing well. Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Combine margarine
and
marshmallow in a large bowl and microwave on High
for
minutes.
Stir
and microwave 1 1/2 minutes longer.
Stir in
Rice Krispies.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish and butter
the
back of spoon to spread.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour the boiling water over Nabisco 100% Bran.
Set aside and allow to cool.
Cream butter and sugar and add the beaten eggs. Sift salt, flour and soda; add to first mixture, then add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add the bran mixture and All-Bran and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in well-buttered muffin pans.

title: caramels
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar and salt, then add corn syrup and mix well.
Add sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring and cook to 245°.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered pan.
When cold, cut into squares and wrap.
Makes about 49 pieces.

title: plantation relish(all measurements are made after ingredients are cut up.)
directions: Pour 1 cup salt over first 6 vegetable ingredients; let stand overnight.
The next morning, drain well; cook cauliflower slightly and separate into small pieces.
Cook sauce until it thickens, then add all ingredients; let come to boil.
Cook about 20 minutes or more.
Place in sterilized jars.
This is delicious with all meats.

title: texas barbecue sandwich
directions: In saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter until tender. Add rest of ingredients, except buns, and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Tear up meat and add to sauce. Toast buns, lightly, heap meat and sauce onto buns and enjoy!!!!!

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix
all ingredients together in bowl.	Refrigerate for 3 hours and serve.
Walnuts can also be added, if desired.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Pour into dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Good breakfast casserole for company.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Melt oleo; saute onions and green pepper.
Add milk and jalapeno cheese on medium heat until melted.
Add crawfish.
Heat on medium heat for 12 to 15 minutes (stir to prevent sticking). Add boiled fettucine and stir well.
Put in 1 large or 2 small casserole dishes and cover with Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Enjoy!

title: pull aparts
directions: Grease a Bundt pan; sprinkle chopped walnuts or pecans on bottom of pan.
Place frozen rolls (18 to 20) on top of nuts; sprinkle half package butterscotch pudding on top of rolls. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Melt together margarine and sugar; pour over rolls.
Let rise all day or night (8 hours).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden.
Tip out of pan immediately.

title: strawberry banana shake
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients except ice.
Process until smooth.
Add ice.
Process again until smooth. Serve immediately.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sour cream, cheese, soup and onions in large bowl.
Add potatoes; mix well.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Toss crumbs and butter; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: Defrost, drain and squeeze chopped spinach.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Line deep dish with pie crust.
Mix beaten eggs, salt, pepper and 3 cheeses with spinach.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake for 45 minutes or until egg is set.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: Mix together and bake in pan 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Brown crushed saltines in butter; set aside.
Drain oysters, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid.
Place half of crumbs in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add oysters, salt and pepper.
Cover with remaining cracker crumbs.
Combine half and half with reserved oyster liquid; pour over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: screwball cake
directions: Mix
together the first 5 ingredients.	Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook onion, celery and pepper (if used) in fat.
Break up tomatoes and crumble in bread.
Add bay leaf, sugar, salt and dry mustard.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with small amount of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: potato dumplings and cabbage(haluske)
directions: Add flour to grated potatoes (enough to make a soft dough). Have a pot of water boiling.
Dip spoon into boiling water and drop dough by small spoonfuls into water.
If spoon is dipped, the dough will not stick to spoon.
Cook minutes, then drain and rinse with hot water.

title: hadgie's rhubarb pie
directions: Sift flour, and add egg and sugar; beat thoroughly.
Add rhubarb.
Add filling in one crust.
Add second crust for a top. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put a little oil in black iron skillet and heat.
Mix all of the ingredients together.
Put in hot pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in a greased pan (black iron skillet is best) at 375° until brown, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
This is good with chili or with soup, beans or turnip greens or all by itself.
It is good hot or cold.

title: ham and turkey rolls
directions: Layer ham, turkey, cheese and broccoli spears and roll.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cream of mushroom or cream of chicken soup, diluted with milk.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen lime-mint salad
directions: In large bowl combine undrained pineapple, dry lime jello, marshmallows and crushed mints.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight until marshmallows soften and melt.
Fold in dessert topping.
Spoon mixture into 16 paper baking cup-lined muffin pans.
Cover and freeze.
Serve on grape or lettuce leaf.

title: baked summer squash
directions: Wash
and trim squash.
Shred with shredder to measure 4 cups. In
a skillet saute onion and squash in 2 tablespoons of the butter, stirring frequently for 10 minutes, or until squash is tender.
Beat
lightly
eggs,
milk, salt and black pepper. Mix with
squash,
onion
and
parsley.
Spread
into
greased shallow 1
quart
baking
dish.
Mix
cracker
crumbs and remaining butter.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until well browned.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms, olives and pimentos and mix all together. Place in large jar or bowl.
Add oil and vinegar to almost cover. Turn jar occasionally.
Refrigerate.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add with buttermilk to dry mixture.
Mix well.

title: mim's onion blossums
directions: Peel onion, leaving root intact.
Cut onion vertically into quarters, cutting to within 1/2-inch of root end.
Cut each quarter vertically into thirds.
Place onion in boiling water for 1 minute; remove and place in ice water for 5 minutes.
Loosen "petals" if necessary.
Drain onion, cut side down.
Place flour in a Ziploc bag; add onion, shaking to coat.
Dip onion in egg.
Place fine cracker crumbs in a Ziploc bag; toss onion to coat.
Chill onion for 1 hour.
Pour oil to depth of 3-inches in an electric fryer or heavy saucepan.
Heat oil to 375°.
Fry onion 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Serve with sauce of your choice.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press into glass pie dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Prepare pudding mix with milk and chill.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Spread on cooled pie shell and add pudding mixture. Use rest of Cool Whip in container to spread over top.

title: marjorie's tortilla rounds
directions: Mix together well.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Slice with sharp knife in 1/2 inch pieces.
(Wet Knife).
Recipe can be doubled.

title: old fashioned raisin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.
Next morning add 2 cups white sugar and 2 well beaten eggs.	Sift together flour and pumpkin pie spices.
Mix into raisin mixture thoroughly.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 60 minutes (or until a toothpick comes out clean).

title: granola
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer cookies on bottom and around sides.
Cut bananas.
Layer cookies and bananas.
Mix or cook pudding.
Pour over cookies and bananas.
Save 3 or 4 wafers.
Mash and put over top of pudding.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Drain.
Combine all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn heat down to simmer and cook without lid for about 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Place in casserole dish. Top with crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix the flour, shortening and salt thoroughly.
Add vinegar, egg and water.
Mix until moistened.
Makes three 9-inch crusts.

title: cherry pie filling
directions: In a saucepan blend in first three ingredients.
Add reserved juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickens and comes to a full boil.
Stir in butter and lemon juice.
Add cherries that were drained.
Cool.

title: veal stew
directions: Shake veal cubes in salt and flour mixture. Brown in butter and Crisco. Add onion, garlic, pepper and broth.
Simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Then add tomato sauce and mushrooms. Serve over hot rice or noodles.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat ingredients together 5 minutes.
Pour in an angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: melt-in-your-mouth dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and baking powder. Let stand for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, scald milk.
Add margarine, sugar and salt.
Cool, then add 2 beaten eggs.
Combine both mixtures with flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 2 hours before serving.
Shape as butterhorns or a pinwheels in muffin pans.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels,
melted
margarine
and
3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Beat together
cream
cheese and 1 cup sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread
on
top
pretzel crust.
Mix large box jello and 2 cups
boiling water until jello dissolved; add frozen strawberries.
Frozen
berries
will cause jello to set up.
Pour over cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated. Yields 12 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat well and add eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour (fold in nuts).
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Nuts are optional.

title: anise cookie teething biscuits
directions: Shape into 2-inch roll; brush with egg.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 400°.
Slice and re-toast until brown.

title: glazed cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients until dough forms; beat 20 strokes.
Turn onto board or cloth dusted with Bisquick.
Roll to coat; knead 10 times. Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2 inch cutter dipped in baking mix.
Bake on greased baking sheet until brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread with Vanilla Glaze while warm.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onions, celery and carrots in melted butter for 10 minutes.
Add peas and flour to sauteed mixture, stirring well. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Combine broth and half and half gradually. Stir in vegetable mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, pepper and chopped chicken.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole. Top with pie crust.
Cut slits for steam to escape. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except ground beef; mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly. Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan; bake for 1 hour.
Drain.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Best if topped with ketchup.

title: granny's cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, undrained pineapple, eggs, baking soda and salt. Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix together 1/2 cup chopped walnuts and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Sprinkle over batter and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Then pour on icing.

title: polly's good dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, store in quart container in refrigerator, will keep up to 3 weeks.

title: sausage-eggs casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear bread into bite size pieces. Layer bread in pan.
Spread cheese over bread.
Add cooked, drained sausage.
Beat eggs, pepper, mustard and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, mix milk with mushroom soup.
Pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or longer, until liquid is absorbed.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix together thoroughly all ingredients, except ginger ale. Chill.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given. Stir until smooth. Pour into an unbaked 8-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 250° and bake for 45 minutes or until set.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; sift together baking soda, baking powder, salt and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in chopped walnuts and apples.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, oleo, flour and cinnamon. Sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt flossie's watermelon pickles
directions: Select thick rind from melon.
Cut green skin and pink flesh away.
Discard.
Cut rind into cubes or thin slices.
Soak overnight in cold water, in the refrigerator, if possible.
Drain. Cover with fresh water and boil 20 minutes until tender.
Drain. Tie spices in bag.
Combine sugar and vinegar; add spice bag and simmer to form a thin syrup.
Add rind and simmer until fruit is clear, about 15 minutes.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars and seal. Makes 6 pints.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Mix peanuts and Rice Krispies together and set aside.
Melt white chocolate (microwave and stir).
Pour melted white chocolate into peanut-Rice Krispies.
Stir well.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, melted oleo and pecans in oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Then add 2nd Layer.

title: barbara's punch
directions: Mix in order given.

title: casserole delicious
directions: Melt butter in rice cooker.
Add everything else; rinse cans with water.
Salt lightly.
Stir together; cover and let cook. When rice cooker cuts off and rice may still feel hard to the taste, add a bit of water and it will finish cooking.

title: cole slaw souffle
directions: Mix jello in hot water.
Add mayonnaise, cold water, salt and vinegar.
Let set until thickens, then whip with mixer.
Add cabbage, celery, onion and green pepper.
Place in 8 x 10 dish. Chill in refrigerator.

title: veggie bars
directions: Cover bottom of 11x17-inch baking pan with crescent roll dough, patting and stretching to fit.
Bake at 350° for 7-8 minutes until light brown.
In mixing bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream, cream cheese, and dressing mix.
Spread over crust in pan.
Combine vegetables, tossing to mix and distribute evenly over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese over vegetables.
Cover with plastic wrap and push vegetables into cheese layer.
Refrigerate covered 3 to 4 hours.
Cut into bars to serve.
(1/2 of recipe may be prepared in 9x13-inch pan.)

title: carrot copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots into rounds.
Add to 2 cups water; cook 10 minutes.
Slice onion thin.
Chop pepper.
Drain carrots; cool and add to onion and pepper in glass or stainless bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour over carrots and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Drain to serve.
Will keep up to 6 weeks in tightly covered glass container in refrigerator.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into both pie shells evenly. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cool, saving broth. In a square baking dish, spread a layer of stuffing mix.
Break chicken into bite-size pieces and put on top of stuffing.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Top with another layer of stuffing mix.
Before baking, pour enough chicken broth over top to moisten the stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and soup mixture is bubbling around edge.

title: provence tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel garlic and cut in tiny pieces. Chop parsley.
Cut tomatoes in half.
Place in oven dish, cut side up.
Sprinkle tomatoes with 2 drops of olive oil, garlic and parsley.
Bake in the oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat juice from cherries and pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O and cream cheese.
Let cool, then add cherries, pineapple, nuts and Coca-Cola last.
Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: apple biscuit basket
directions: Butter aluminum pie pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread out biscuits as far as they stretch.
Butter them, then put spoonful of uncooked apples on top, then a little brown sugar.
Fold over and seal edges to make miniature pies.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper.
Drain and add cooked noodles and sour cream.

title: lucy's brownies
directions: Mix all.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Bake in ungreased pan.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Layer the
ingredients	as
listed:
rice,
corn, salt, pepper, tomato sauce,
water, onion, bell pepper, ground beef, tomato sauce, water
and
bacon into a large casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and peppers.
Drain off grease. Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks and whole egg.
Beat in cold water and salt. Stir in flour.
Roll out and let dry.
Cut into strips and let dry out.
After dried out, cook in beef or chicken broth.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in buttered baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and eggs.
Spread over apples.
Pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: ukoy
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, m.s.g. and pepper. Beat egg until foamy.
Add flour mixture and water.
Mix until smooth.
Add mongo sprouts, tofu, squash and green onion.
Mix well.

title: coconut eggs
directions: Mix
first
3 ingredients in saucepan and cook to 250°, stirring.
Beat
egg
whites
to
peaks
and
then beat in hot syrup, slowly.
Add coconut.
If it seems dry, add a few drops of water.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet,
cool
and	form in eggs. Coat with melted chocolate chips.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Remove wing tips and reserve for another use, such as soup. Cut wings apart at joint.
Brown wings in oven or in a skillet with small amount of oil.
Drain off all excess fat.

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl with mixer, cream margarine, sugar and Sweet 'N Low brown sugar substitute.
Beat in peanut butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and peanuts.
On baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, with a tablespoon, drop dough 2 inches apart.
With a fork dipped in flour, press a crisscross pattern on each cookie.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 18 cookies.
Each contains 110 calories.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: (Some people desire to leave peelings on their cucumbers.)

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk and Key lime juice.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: malted milk ball cookies
directions: For each cookie, roll 1 teaspoon dough around malted milk ball until smooth. Roll in coconut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Repeat with remaining dough, candy and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen and contains about 75 calories each.

title: grilled spicy chicken breast fillets(low calorie)
directions: In a small bowl, combine first seven ingredients.
Mix well. Set aside.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in the warm water.
Add sugar, shortening and soda to the warm milk, then add to yeast mixture.
Add flour to make soft dough; knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Cover with cloth and let rest 10 or 15 minutes.
Roll and cut or shape into desired shapes.
Put in greased, warm pans.
Let rise until doubled in a warm place.
Bake in a 375° to 400° oven.
Brush with butter or oleo.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix first four ingredients thoroughly.
Sift together remaining ingredients and stir in.
Chill dough, roll into balls the size of large walnuts.
Coat with granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.
If you underbake cookies they stay soft.
If you overbake they become hard like gingersnaps.

title: garden minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage about 1/2 inch thick; brown in oil in Dutch oven.
Add garlic, onion, carrots and basil; cook 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes with liquid, bouillon, cabbage, water, salt and pepper.
Bring soup to boil; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes. Add beans (undrained) and cook another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir milk, sugar, shortening, salt and four cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise one hour; knead again.
Make loaves; put in greased pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and oil to a rolling boil until sugar dissolves.
Set aside to cool.
Drain canned vegetables; mix with remaining ingredients.
Add vinegar mixture and refrigerate overnight.
You just continue to add vegetable ingredients to the marinade as the salad is eaten.
Keeps well for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: nut macaroons
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, while beating constantly.
Fold in chopped pecans and sprinkle with salt.
Drop from tip of spoon 1-inch apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in
a moderate oven (350°) until delicately browned.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion, potato and carrot in oil or fat in a large saucepan until onion is golden brown and tender.
Add water, oregano, basil, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and boil for 12 minutes longer, until spaghetti is tender.
Serve sprinkled with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes four servings, about 1 cup each.

title: rice fritters(lummur)
directions: Put fruit in blender and blend.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into ice cream maker.
Milk should reach about 2 to 3 inches from the top.
(Mixture should be slightly sweeter than ice cream will be when finished.) Run ice cream maker according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together the sour cream and cream cheese.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: oatmeal and applesauce cookies
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, spices, oatmeal and raisins. Add applesauce, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix just to moisten.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: taco hamburger casserole
directions: Crumble beef into ovenware dish.
Cook in microwave 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Stir after 3 minutes. Set aside.
Place butter in a 1-quart measuring cup.
Cook until melted.
Add onions.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Add Tabasco sauce, tomato sauce, taco seasoning and water.
Stir. Combine eggs and half and half.
Add this slowly to tomato sauce, stirring constantly.
Place half of the corn chips in casserole dish.
Top with half of beef, half of Mozzarella and half of sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cook 15 minutes.
Top with sour cream and shredded cheese.
Cover.
Cook 1 to 3 minutes.

title: golden chicken rolls
directions: Flatten chicken with meat mallet.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese on each.
Roll up like jelly roll, folding in sides to hold in ham and cheese.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake in shallow roasting pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cheese pastry:
Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften at room temperature; blend together.
Stir in flour; chill about 1 hour.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in greased 1 1/4-inch muffin pans.
Press dough against bottom and sides.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Form in rolls and chill.
Slice and bake 10 minutes on light greased cookie sheet at about 375°.

title: corn fritters(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add milk, eggs and corn; stir until combined.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls into 375° oil and deep fry, turning once, until golden.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Add next 6 ingredients, mix lightly.
Pour into casserole. Prepare mashed potatoes, using package directions.
Spoon around edges of casserole.
Sprinkle potatoes with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: orange-cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fruit compote
directions: Heat together prunes, ginger ale, dried apricots, raisins, orange juice, ginger and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain pineapple and pears. Slice pear halves into quarters.
Gently mix fruit and syrup into fruit mixture, stirring with rubber spatula.
Serve either warm or chilled.
Great for Christmastime.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together. Spread 1/2 stick melted butter in dish.
Pour in batter. Pour fruit with a little juice on top, 1 to 2 cups.
Bake at 350° until done.
Add ice cream on top when served.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar and syrup in a 2 to 3-quart microwave dish.
Stir and cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir and cook on High 4 minutes again.
Add butter (no substitute).
Stir and cook 3 minutes on High.
Add soda and vanilla in that order; stir.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet and spread thin.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place a layer of thinly sliced onions in a greased baking dish, about 1/3 of the depth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dust with flour.
Add a layer of thinly sliced potatoes; season.
Dot with butter; moisten with milk.
Place breaded pork chops on top. Bake at 350° until done.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add baby food plums, red food coloring and flour.
If flour is plain add salt, soda, cloves, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour into well greased Bundt pan.
Cook 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix together and cook about 10 minutes, stirring often.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and pepper.
Drain off grease; combine the rest of the ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or may be made the night before and placed in crock-pot on medium.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: In saucepan, prepare macaroni.
Add vegetables for last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In same pan, stir soup into cream cheese.
Add milk, mustard, cheese and pepper.
Over low heat, heat until cream cheese is melted, stirring often.
Add macaroni.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked rice and mushrooms casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour ingredients in dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: breast of chicken, parmigiana
directions: Cut up chicken (chunks) and place in bottom of 8 x 11-inch flat cake pan.
Add dash of salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cover with sliced cheese, then sauce and grated cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave salsa
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, mix tomatoes, onion and garlic. Add green pepper, lemon juice, and seasonings.
Mix well. Microwave on high for 45-60 seconds until heated through.
Serve immediately with chips.
Can be stored in refrigerator for 3 days.

title: butter balls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together in mixer bowl.
Add butter and vanilla, mixing well with a pastry blender.
Stir in pecans. Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Check at halftime to see if they are baking okay.
Roll warm cookies in confectioners sugar; cool and roll in confectioners sugar again.

title: sunshine and shadow squares
directions: Cream margarine; add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, water and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and soda; mix well.
Spread in greased 10 x 14-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips over batter.
Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks; add 1 cup brown sugar and spread over batter. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil.
Blend ingredients together, then add raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased pan.
After first hour, cover with foil to prevent drying.

title: oscar mayer smokies in sauce
directions: Mix flour with water for thickening paste.
Cook Smokies in sauce on low heat for at least 2 hours; longer if there is plenty of time.

title: diet sweet and sour chicken
directions: Heat in hot skillet or wok the oil until hot.
Add chicken and stir-fry a few minutes.
Add garlic, celery, sweet pepper and bean sprouts; toss to coat.
Drain pineapple (save juice).
Toss pineapple with chicken-vegetables until mixed.
In a bowl, mix pineapple juice, vinegar, ginger, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve with rice, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: crab delights
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cut muffins in quarters.
Spread topping.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Muffins should be crisp on the bottom.

title: transylvania sour beans
directions: Cook beans in salted water until tender. Drain and save 1 cup of the liquid. Fry bacon until crisp. Break into coarse pieces and add to beans. Brown the flour in bacon drippings. Add slowly the liquid from the beans, also the vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper, stirring constantly, until smooth. Add beans and simmer a few minutes.
Serve with roast.

title: lemon refrigerator cake
directions: Let Jell-O, sugar, lemon juice and boiling water set until light jelling and then whip.
Whip Carnation milk (ice cold); whip Jell-O and milk separate, then together.
Put in cracker crust. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on the top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs well. Add melted chocolate and butter; mix well.
Add flour.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crockpot macaroni & cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put into lightly greased crock pot. Cut thin slices of cheese and put on top. Cook 3-4 hour on low.

title: field peas
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and crumble.
Brown onion in bacon fat.
Add flour and brown.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water and blend into flour mixture.
Season to taste. Add peas; cover and cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Top with crumbled bacon before serving.

title: layered spinach - lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 8 ingredients in order listed in a large salad bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and salad dressing mix. Mix well.
Spread over top of salad, sealing to edge of bowl. Cover tightly and refrigerate for several hours or overnight. "Yum-yum."

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, margarine, sugar and egg over medium-high heat until thick and frothy (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Stir frequently. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
When cool enough to handle, drop by teaspoonfuls into 10x sugar and roll into balls.
Flavor improves overnight.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Stir tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Add beans.
Arrange lasagna noodle halves in bottom of baking dish; spread half of the meat mixture and cheese; repeat with remaining noodles, meat and cheese.
Cover and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and place corn chips in border atop of the casserole.
Heat 10 minutes uncovered.
Serve with lettuce, tomato wedges, corn chips, salsa and sour cream.

title: fudge jumbles
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Spread 2/3 in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling over oatmeal.
Spoon small spoonfuls of oatmeal mixture on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dieter's de-liteful dessert
directions: Spray 8-inch square pan lightly with Pam.
Prepare Jell-O as directed.
Pour in pan and let set.
Slice bananas and place on top of Jell-O.
Prepare instant pudding as directed; pour over bananas.
Let set 10 minutes in refrigerator.
Drain crushed pineapple; place over pudding.
Top with whipped NutriWhip.

title: fast cream cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, mash cream cheese with potato masher. Add can of crushed pineapple (drained), sugar and Cool Whip. Mix and pour into pie crust. Spread to fill pan. Garnish with sliced pineapple. Refrigerate 2 hours. Takes less than 5 minutes preparation time. Serves 6.

title: tomato pie
directions: Line a pie tin with a very rich biscuit dough, then fill with sliced tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Then mix cheese, mayonnaise and onion and spread over tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot with sliced cold roast beef or ham and cole slaw.

title: grandma wese coleslaw
directions: Dice green onions. Rinse the bag of chopped cabbage;
mix together. Crunch Ramen noodles; pour on top of cabbage. Add sunflower seeds and almonds. Toss all together. Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and the 2
(ramen noodle) seasoning packets. Pour on top of the coleslaw, mix. Let sit for 1 hour. When ready to serve, mix again.

title: green rice
directions: Melt cheese in microwave until heated through.
Mix together all remaining ingredients in casserole dish.
Add cheese and mix again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: casserole onion bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to first mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Let rise until double (about 45 minutes).
Stir down and turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole that has been well-greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in butter, reduce heat and cook until done. Remove from fat.
Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Add flour, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and bouillon.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and beef; heat it but don't let sour cream boil.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a boil. Let cool.
Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight.

title: hearty italian bean soup
directions: In large pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.

Add chopped carrots, diced celery, chopped onion and 1/2 cup chicken broth. Cover and cook until vegetables are very tender, about 15 minutes. Stir in remaining chicken broth and tomatoes, breaking tomatoes up with a spoon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in white and red kidney beans and zucchini.
Simmer until zucchini is tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in spinach.
Cook until tender, about 3 minutes.

title: deviled swiss steak
directions: In large skillet, saute onions and garlic in shortening or oil until golden brown.
Remove onions.
Dredge pieces of steak in seasoned flour.
Saute until well browned.

title: dean's white chocolate clusters
directions: Melt bark in microwave.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon out on wax paper and let cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and arrange in dish.
Cook chicken and cut up; add to broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli; sprinkle on shredded cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and melted butter (mixed together). Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.

title: texas redanda longneck(chili)
directions: In a heavy pan, heat oil and brown beef cubes evenly. Add all the remaining ingredients. Simmer chili for 1 hour. Add a little flour paste or Masa Harina if chili is too thin.
Add more chili powder if you like it spicy.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat, celery, pepper and onion; drain. Combine all ingredients together in a large pot and simmer on low for 30 to 40 minutes or cook in crock-pot, if you prefer.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt oleo and let cool to room temperature.
Beat eggs and add flour and sugars, mixing well.
Add cooled oleo and vanilla and beat well.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: sunshine carrot salad
directions: Mayonnaise may be substituted for sour cream.
Combine all ingredients except sour cream or mayonnaise.
Chill 2 or 3 hours. Stir in sour cream just before serving.

title: crunchy frozen punch
directions: This
punch may be prepared well in advance. Color of Jell-O determines punch color.

title: chicken parm
directions: Mix Shake 'n Bake, Parmesan cheese and oregano in a bag.
Add chicken breasts and shake.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Take out and pour spaghetti sauce over chicken. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: frosting(like whipped cream)
directions: Mix milk and flour.
Cook in saucepan until thick.
Add shortening, oleo, sugar and vanilla to flour mixture and beat until light and frothy.

title: pressure cooker ribs and kraut
directions: Stir together caraway seed, sugar, onion and kraut.
In 6-quart pressure cooker, layer spareribs, sauerkraut mixture, potatoes and carrots.
Season with salt.
(Cooker should be no more than 2/3 full.)
