Measure reserved sauerkraut liquid and add water to measure 1 cup.
Pour into cooker.
Cover; cook about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine ingredients (except pie shell) in large bowl.
Pour in shell and bake in oven for 15 minutes. Then reduce to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Knife inserted near edge comes out clean.)
Cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hamburger by the yard
directions: About
minutes before dinner, start heating oven to 350°. In
a
large bowl mix all ingredients except cheese and bread. Spread
mixture evenly on cut side of bread.
Bake for 35 minutes. Cut cheese slices into thirds.
Arrange on top of meat.
Bake another 5 minutes or until cheese starts to melt.

title: church supper chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in three or four large kettles.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove the bay leaves before serving.
Makes 75 servings.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to an even thickness of 1/3-inch.
Do not pound the tenderloins.
Grate the yellow zest from the lemons using a fine grater and squeeze the juice from the lemons.
Combine the lemon zest and juice with the wine, garlic, shallots, rosemary, oregano, salt and pepper in a glass or stainless steel bowl.
Add the chicken breasts and marinate for 2 hours at room temperature or up to 8 hours refrigerated, tightly covered with plastic wrap.

title: secret cake
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Cook margarine, Crisco, water and cocoa together.
Boil and pour over sugar and flour mixture. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in sheet cake pan.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring water or broth to a boil.
Add broccoli and onion.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, cream and butter. Stir and heat to boiling.
Slowly add cold water to flour, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Slowly add to soup mixture, stirring rapidly.
Cook and stir until soup is thickened.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: no fail divinity candy
directions: Put sugar, water and syrup in pan.
Stir while it dissolves over heat.
Let boil, without stirring, to a hard ball stage. While syrup is cooking, beat the egg whites.
When syrup is ready, pour over the egg whites slowly, beating constantly.
Add pecans and flavor; beat until cool and drop by spoonfuls on buttered plate.

title: breaded venison chops
directions: Beat egg together with water.
Dip venison chops in egg mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Brown 10 to 15 minutes, on each side.
Add cream of mushroom soup thinned with 1/2 soup can of water.
Simmer for 35 minutes or until done.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir brownie mix, eggs, oil and water in a large bowl until well blended.
Fold in white chocolate.
Spread in greased pan; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 25 to 28 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat to creamy consistency. Stir in pineapple, 1 cup nuts, green pepper, onion and seasoning salt. Chill 1/2 hour. Roll in remaining 1 cup nuts. Chill until ready to serve.

title: marinated vegetables(makes about 4 cups)
directions: Place vegetables in shallow dish.
In small bowl or jar, mix remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover; refrigerate 6 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: quick fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: homos btahani
directions: Blend chickpeas in food processor.
Add tahini, lemon juice, salt and garlic powder to taste.
Blend until smooth.
Garnish with oil on top and parsley.
Serve with pita bread as a dip.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Use a platter or small tray.
Mix green onions into refried beans.
Layer onto platter, follow with layer of olives and layer of guacamole.
Add layer of diced tomatoes and layer of Cheddar, Jack or combination of both cheeses.
Spoon chile dip over the top.
Don't use too much as it makes the consistency too watery. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: refrigerator cucumber pickles(good for 9 months)
directions: Mix together in 1/2 gallon jar.
Cover with Saran for as long as it lasts.
(Do not cook.)
Shake up two or three times a day as long as they last.
They are ready to eat after 3 days.
Very good and crisp.
This can be doubled, but use a larger container.
Saran Wrap keeps lid from rusting.

title: oriental spareribs
directions: Wash and dry spareribs.
Meanwhile, combine rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Marinate ribs at least 1 hour or overnight.
In skillet, wok or Dutch oven, brown ribs in 2 tablespoons oil.
When slightly brown, pour the marinade over, reduce heat to a simmer, cover and cook 40 minutes, turning twice during cooking period.
When ribs are ready, they should be orangey-brown in color.
Serve immediately with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into 10-inch buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Serve plain or with whipped topping.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass, rectangular baking pan.
Add buttered bread to cover bottom and sides of pan, crusts along edge. (Do not break bread slices.)
Sprinkle cheese evenly over the bread.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon evenly over the cheese.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs, salt, pepper, mustard and milk.
Pour over bread, cheese and bacon to cover all.
Refrigerate overnight (at least 8 hours).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let set 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: chipper tuna casserole
directions: Empty soup into casserole.
Add milk and stir until well mixed.
Add drained tuna.
Add 3/4 cup of the potato chips and the cup of peas.
Mix.
Sprinkle remaining potato chips on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: candy cake
directions: Mix the sugar, cream and syrup together and cook to soft ball stage.
Add the corn flakes, Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Press firmly into cake pan.

title: fancy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in medium casserole dish.
Crumble 1 cup Ritz crackers, mix with 1/2 stick melted oleo and put on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pat's cottage pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Measure flour by dip-level-pour method and by sifting.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt in bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Beat until smooth. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm, cut in 3-inch squares, with hot vanilla, lemon or nutmeg sauce.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cabbage, carrot, green pepper and onion.
To prepare dressing, stir together mayonnaise or salad dressing, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt.
Pour the dressing over the cabbage mixture; toss lightly to coat vegetables.
Cover and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: key lime chiffon pie
directions: Mix together condensed milk, egg yolks and grated rind.
Beat the egg whites very stiff and add sugar a little at a time, beating it in as for a meringue (reserve for later use).
Add lime juice into the milk mixture and stir until thick.
Fold this into the beaten whites, blending gently but thoroughly.
Turn this into a pre-baked, cooled pie shell and chill for several hours before serving.
There is absolutely no cooking of the filling.
Can also put filling in parfaits as for Key Lime Mousse and chill.

title: chicken-parmesan pizzas(low-fat)
directions: Heat grill. Mix oil, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Brush on both sides of chicken. Grill chicken 8 to 10 minutes, turning once, until opaque in center. Remove to a cutting board; cool slightly, then cut crosswise in strips. Spread about 1/2 cup of the tomatoes on each bread shell to within 1/2-inch of edges. Top each with chicken and Mozzarella. Grill 2 minutes; cover grill and cook 2 minutes longer or until Mozzarella melts. Top with basil and Parmesan cheese.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, crisco & sugar. Add egg yolks beat until creamy. Combine flour, soda & salt. Add alternately with buttermilk. Mix well for 2 minutes, add vanilla. Fold in egg whites (beaten), coconut and pecans. Makes 3 layers in 9 inch pans. Bake 20 to 25 minutes on 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Note:
I cook mine in a black skillet.
May use other, just be sure it is large enough.

title: egg brunch casserole(from beth's mom)
directions: Mix croutons with crumbled sausage.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped onion, then cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over cheese. Cover and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine beef, onion, bread crumbs, egg, applesauce, salt, pepper and sauce.
Shape in loaf pan.
Put ketchup and brown sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with crushed corn flakes.
Pour salad mixture on top of corn flakes.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar, nutmeg, butter, milk and egg.
Beat vigorously with spoon for 1/2 minute.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.
Immediately roll in 1/2 cup melted margarine and then in a mixture of 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Serve warm.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: For each hamburger cookie, spread 1/2 teaspoon icing on flat side of vanilla wafer.
Place 1 teaspoon coconut and 1 mint cookie on frosting.
Spread flat side of second vanilla wafer with 1/2 teaspoon icing.
Place frosting side down on mint cookie.
Brush top of "hamburger" with honey; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Repeat to make 5 more cookies.
Yields 6 cookies.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Beat half and half, eggs and flour.
Rinse chiles and split open.
Take the seeds out.
Grate the cheeses; save for the topping.
Make layers of chiles, cheeses and egg mixture.
Top with remaining cheese and tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour 1/2 of batter into a thick greased pan.
Put on top grated cheese and jalapeno.
Pour on rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine ingredients and freeze in 5 or 7 ounce clear plastic cups.
Use microwave to thaw about 30 seconds or take out of freezer about 20 minutes before serving.

title: microwave pickles
directions: Slice cucumber in very thin slices.
Cook 7 minutes on medium. Stir twice.

title: blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Heat butter
to
bubbling
in
saucepan.
Do not brown. Put egg
yolks,
lemon	juice,	salt and cayenne into electric blender container.	Cover
and quickly flick motor on and off. Remove cover, turn
motor	on high and immediately add the hot butter in a
steady
stream
slowly.	When
all
the butter is added, turn off
motor.
Keep
sauce
warm by setting the container in a saucepan
containing 2 inches warm water.
Do not let water boil. Makes 3/4 cup or enough to serve 4.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet with oil.
Add all but rice; bring to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Before serving, add rice and heat through.
Take out bay leaf and serve.
Serves 8.

title: gloria pitzer's garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Beat with mixer at high speed, not quite 1 minute, until smooth.
Batter should be thick enough to drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
If too thin, add more self-rising flour until it will make shaggy looking soft mounds.
Remove beaters.
Use rubber scraper to streak the dough with 1/4 cup Kraft grated American cheese food.

title: angel food pie(servings:  4)
directions: Mix together crushed pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice. When boiling, add cornstarch, which has been mixed with water. Stir constantly until thickened.
Cool completely.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Then fold into mixture.
Put in baked pie shell and cover with whipped cream and chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: witte's pudding pie
directions: Mix milk, ice cream and pudding mix in a bowl.
Pour into an already graham pie crust.
Put in fridge for 2 hours.
Take out of fridge.
Top with Cool Whip and chocolate morsels.
Serve immediately.
Yummy, yummy, good!

title: nine-layer salad
directions: In a large bowl, break up lettuce. Then layer the celery, pepper, onion and peas. Slice the hard-boiled eggs on top. Mix the sugar with the mayonnaise or salad dressing and spread over top of the eggs. Sprinkle the cheddar cheese and bacon on the top of the dressing. Cover.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray. Cook over medium heat the onion, pepper, celery and garlic. Saute until tender. Stir in beans, tomato, water, chili powder, pepper and hot sauce. Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Place rice in 1-quart casserole and pour bean mixture on top. Sprinkle with cheese and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil berries, water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O, stir to dissolve.
Cool, then add other ingredients. Chill to set, then serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookies on 14-inch pizza pan and bake according to directions until golden brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Cool completely.
Mix cheese and Cool Whip together and spread on the cold cookie layer.
Decorate with fruit, starting with the strawberries kiwi, peaches, bananas and blueberries in the middle. Place these fruits in a circle around the pizza.
Sprinkle with Fruit Fresh.
Refrigerate.
Serves many.

title: vintage grandma's turkey stuffing(20 pound turkey)
directions: Cube toasted bread.
Add all other ingredients together with toasted bread, except broth.
Pour hot turkey broth over the dry mix.
Toss to moisten completely then use to stuff turkey.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place prepared chicken, vegetables and seasonings in a large soup kettle.
Cover with hot water.
Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down to medium low; simmer slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May have to add 1 more cup water.
Remove chicken from broth.
Drain broth back in pan.
Place chicken on a plate.
Put in fridge to cool. Remove skin after cool.
Remove meat from bones and return to broth.
Bring to boil again.
Add noodles.
Turn to simmer until noodles are tender.
Add 1 tablespoon parsley flakes.
Enjoy!

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Line casserole with apples and cranberries and sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Melt margarine; add oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and pecans.
Mix together and spread on top of apples and cranberries. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great at Thanksgiving and Christmas!

title: chocolate cinnamon cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Bring to a boil the butter, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost.

title: meatball in a minute stew
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients to make mini meatballs (24 approximately).
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Pour grease off.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in oven for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 cup sugar and pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: girl scout mints
directions: Melt chocolate over steam of hot water.
Mix in peppermint. Hand dip crackers.
You may remove excess by scraping on edge of pan.
Coated crackers must be placed on wax paper to harden.

title: party mix recipe
directions: Can add nuts and pretzels.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Spread pizza crust onto large pizza pan.
Place cooked egg substitute on crust.
Top with mushrooms, cheeses, pepper, onions and meat.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until brown and cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter in large pan (will boil higher). Stir frequently to keep from burning (medium heat) for 7 to 8 minutes.
When mixture has boiled, drop a small amount into cold water.
If a small ball forms, remove pan from heat.
Add Marshmallow Fluff and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Spread in a buttered dish.
After it hardens, cut into squares.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain off grease.
Add all ingredients to hamburger in this order.
Serve over wide noodles.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape meat in a loaf (round or long).
Bake 1 hour at 350° or approximately until done.

title: skillet chicken with wine
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Slice onions.
Cut potatoes into 2-inch chunks.
Remove skin and fat from chicken.

title: frittata
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in 300° oven in glass pan for 1 hour.
If using a metal pan, bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy microwave chocolate pudding
directions: Take the persimmon pulp that has been run through a colander and add sugar, melted butter, eggs, sour milk with 1/3 teaspoon soda dissolved in it and flour.
Bake in a moderate oven.
Prepare syrup.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Mix together in a saucepan.
We put this on top of homemade ice cream.
Makes a big batch.

title: glorified grahams
directions: Place the graham crackers in a single layer on a cookie sheet. Mix the margarine and sugar together and pour over the graham crackers.
Sprinkle the pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: creamy chicken fettuccine
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat the oil.
Add chicken and cook over medium heat until tender, 2 to 3 minutes each side. Remove chicken from skillet and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Set aside.
In same skillet, combine mushrooms and garlic.
Cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, for 1 minute.
Sprinkle with flour and stir quickly to combine.
Continue to stir.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese and pepper.
Return chicken to skillet and cook, stirring frequently, until chicken is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
To serve on serving platter, arrange fettuccine and top with chicken mixture.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Melt margarine; add sugar, then beaten egg.
Add this to dissolved yeast mixture.
Add flour; stir until well mixed.
Place in refrigerator in an airtight bowl.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually); egg and vanilla, beat well. Add dry ingredients and mix.
In small portions roll dough out thin and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes until edges are slightly golden brown.
Cool on rack.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Mix first 4
ingredients.
Add	remaining and freeze in paper cups placed in muffin tin.

title: won-stir fry
directions: Marinate steak for 30 minutes with worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and dijon mustard.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chicken and chips in pan.
In skillet, saute onion and chilies in butter.
Add soups and cheese. Cook until melted.
Pour over chicken and chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: good morning casserole
directions: Mix eggs, spices and milk together. Add sausage and stir well. Set aside.

title: condensed milk
directions: Mix nonfat milk and water well.
Set in a pan of hot water and stir in sugar.
Stir well to dissolve the sugar.
This equals 1 can of sweetened condensed milk.
Keep refrigerated.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with bay leaf in salted water.
Drain and remove bay leaf; cool.
Peel potatoes and grate coarsely.
Add melted margarine to mixture; blend until smooth.
Blend in sour cream, salt, pepper, onions and 1 1/2 cups cheese.

title: chicken tandoori
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread over chicken.
Marinate at least 12 hours.
Bake for 45 minutes at 425°. Also may be cooked on an outdoor grill.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients carefully.
Don't shake them up.
Just make sure they're combined.
You can add food coloring, if you like.

title: white grape salad
directions: Wash grapes and cut in half.
Add about 1 oz. pineapple juice to cream cheese to reach the consistency of thick soup, then pour on top of grapes.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Toss until completely coated.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve.

title: sugarless spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Blend flour, soda, spice and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or cool whip.

title: sticky buns
directions: In each section of a muffin pan, place 1/4 teaspoon butter or margarine, 1 tablespoon molasses or syrup and a sprinkling of nuts.
Place the rolls upside down into each section. Bake according to directions.
Remove from pan immediately. Drizzle sticky buns with molasses mixture left in pan.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour gradually with nuts.
Make crescent or round.
Placed on greased cookie sheet. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.
Sprinkle while hot with confectioners sugar.
May shake inside paper bag.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese in a bowl.
Add sugar.
In another bowl, beat milk until light and fluffy.
Add lime jello, cream cheese and sugar mixture.
Pour into pan lined with graham cracker crust, pineapple and cherries on crust.
Place in refrigerator and let chill overnight.
Nuts may be sprinkled on top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Mix well. Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 9 x 9-inch dish. Let set.
Spread sour cream on top.
Add remaining jello.
Chill.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook hamburg, onion and green pepper until done.
Add sauces and tomato paste.
Cook macaroni until done.
Drain and add hamburg mixture.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, oleo and chopped nuts.
Mix as pie dough.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in water. Add 7-Up. Cool until slightly thickened. Add pineapple, bananas, and marshmallows. Pour into 13 x 9 inch dish. Chill until firm and spread with topping.

title: frozen strawberry tarts
directions: Drain strawberries and reserve juice.
Prepare Dream Whip with milk and vanilla as directed on package.
Mix condensed milk, lemon juice, almond extract and strawberries plus 3 tablespoons reserved juice.
Blend in prepared Dream Whip.
Spoon into tart shells and freeze at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: hallelujah ring
directions: In two separate bowls, prepare jellos according to directions using a little less boiling water.
In one, cool with ice cubes; in the other, cool slightly and add the sour cream.
Chill until thickened like cake batter.
Peel, seed, drain and slice fruit. Add half to each jello and the nuts to the jello and sour cream. Pour in layers into a lightly oiled mold or Bundt pan and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold on a platter of greens and garnish with fresh fruit.

title: spicy orange pecans
directions: Combine egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar and the orange juice. Add pecans; coat well.
Drain and roll in well mixed dry ingredients.
Separate nuts on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° until dry.
Turn off oven when dry, so they do not burn.

title: pork 'n' bean bread
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients until combined.
Fill 5 greased and floured 16-ounce cans 2/3 full of batter.
Place cans on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool before removing from cans.
Also can bake in two 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: praline cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Sift through colander until no lumps remain.
Add beaten egg whites; mix.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on heavily greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for about 35 minutes.

title: tootie's cake
directions: Bake the cake in sheet pan. After baking, punch holes in cake and pour the Eagle Brand milk over cake while hot.
Add the pineapple and coconut.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Cut sugar into cream cheese (cream cheese should be at room temperature). Add oil and color; hand knead until smooth. You are now ready to mold candies or cut if you desire. Candy may be frozen in molded or unmolded state.
(When molding candy, use rubber candy molds, not plastic.)

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let bread thaw and rise.
Cut into 2 parts.
Roll out; spread with egg and grated Parmesan.
Spread with pepperoni.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Roll and put on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven or until golden brown.

title: berry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place berries in baking pan.
Sprinkle with enough sugar to sweeten.
Mix butter, oats, brown sugar and flour together until crumbly.
Sprinkle over berries.
Bake for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package and drain.
Add onions, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix crackers with melted margarine.
Put on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Foil cookie sheet.
Cook ribs on sheet at 400° for 20 minutes. Drip grease off ribs.
Put spareribs in crock-pot.
Add onions and barbecue sauce.
Cook all day on low.

title: beef and bean enchiladas
directions: Brown meat; add soup and sauce to meat.
Soften tortillas in small amount of hot oil, then place 2 tablespoons mixture in center of tortilla and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese and roll up and place in oven-proof dish.
Pour remainder of mixture on top and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a casserole, stir soup and soy sauce.
Mix half of the onions with the beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more.

title: bear claws
directions: You will also need waxed paper.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface with floured cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet until they spring back (do not overbake).
Frost and decorate.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: applesauce raisin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except raisins.
Do not use electric mixer.
Add raisins last.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. Makes 3 dozen muffins.

title: forget me cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy (have at room temperature).
Add salt.
Gradually add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating mixture until stiff peaks form.
Fold vanilla, chocolate morsels and pecans into beaten egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Place in oven and turn off heat.
Do not open oven door for at least 8 hours.
Carefully remove cookies from foil.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: hot ham and pasta salad
directions: Mix together and serve hot on lettuce, garnished with tomato wedges.
Delicious refrigerated and served cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 cup water and add to sugar mixture.
Cook on low heat 10 minutes or until clear.
Add salt, jello and juice.
(Add red cake coloring if desired.)
Cool slightly, then add fresh strawberries. Fill baked pie shell.

title: turkey enchilada casserole
directions: Brown turkey and onion in skillet; drain.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with sauce.
Layer tortillas, turkey, cheese and sour cream.
Repeat.
Top the dish with tortillas, remainder of sauce, cheese, olives and scallions.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: orange no-bake cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add wafers, juice, vanilla and nuts. Make into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed: lettuce, celery, eggs, peas, green pepper, onion and bacon.
Mix sugar with mayonnaise; put over other ingredients. Sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise; let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Set aside.
Dissolve yeast and water.
Mix in flour, sugar and salt.
Mix, then add melted shortening.
Roll out 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Dip each biscuit on both sides in melted oleo.
Leave all in the pan.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and beat.
Add syrup, melted butter, pecans, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes in a 400° oven, then lower heat to 350° and bake until firm on top.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Early in day:
In bowl with wire whisk, beat 2 tablespoons melted margarine with milk, flour, salt and 3 eggs.
Refrigerate 2 hours to allow flour to absorb liquid for a tender crepe.
With mixer at medium speed, beat cheeses, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg until smooth.
Brush 7-inch crepe pan with melted margarine; heat over medium heat.
Pour in scant 1/4 cup batter.
Cook 1 minute until top is set.
Invert onto waxed paper.
Repeat.

title: death by chocolate 2
directions: Bake sheet cake according to package directions.
While warm, poke holes in cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour condensed milk over cake.
Cover cake with crumbled candy bars. Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill several hours.

title: low-fat pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Add flour, lite salt and sugar.
Mix well.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; arrange in dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine soup, curry powder, mayo and lemon juice; pour over top of chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Crumble breads; add all other ingredients except margarine. Pour into crock-pot; dot with oleo.
Cover and cook on high for two hours or on low for 3 to 4 hours.
If you want to add chicken, cook in pot on stove in salted water until done (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Cool, then debone and put chicken in with the dressing in crock-pot.
Makes about 16 (6 ounce) servings.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Drain off pineapple juice.
Save for dressing.
Mix jello and 2 cups hot water, then add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Add oranges, pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Let set until firm.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients & chill. 1/2 cup of pecans can be added for additional flavor, or cherries can be added for color.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix in bowl; cover and refrigerate for 4 days.
Mix each day. On the fourth day, pat out on board to get out air bubbles. Divide into equal parts; roll into sausage shapes in desired sizes.
Place in broiling pan; bake for 5 hours at 175°.
Let stand in oven additional hour after turning off.
Let cool, wrap and freeze.

title: george's favorite cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Then pour sugar, water and salt over them.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Take out and drain 40 minutes. Then mix with sour cream and toss.

title: tuna cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften for 1 hour.
Drain tuna; mash with fork.
Combine cream cheese, tuna and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry and salt; mix.
Add onion; stir to blend.
Chill 1 hour.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and pat dry.
Grease skin of potatoes and bake in a 400° oven until done.
Split the potatoes in half.
Take the potato out and mash, then cream with a little sweet milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Put back into the shell.
Top with slices of cheese and bake in oven until slightly brown and bubbling hot.

title: clara's cornbread pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: rocky road pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Cool.
Heat peanut butter and chocolate chips in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat stirring constantly just until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
Fold in marshmallows.
Cool 10 minutes.
Spoon and spread 1/2 cup marshmallow mixture in pie shell.
Lightly pack half of ice cream into pie shell.

title: the wright's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in oil and drain.
Put into a pot and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring often. (I cook mine in a crock-pot.)
Cook spaghetti and serve.

title: mamich's barbecue sauce from north carolina
directions: Melt butter, add vinegar, then add other ingredients and bring to boil.
Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
This is good on pork ribs or chicken.
Baste during last half of cooking meat.
Recipe may be halved, it's still good!

title: david's meal
directions: Mix raw meat, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and bread or crackers.
If you use bread, soak it in water.
Squeeze it out and break into small pieces before using.
If you use crackers, crush them first.
Form small balls.
Brown in pan on all sides and then add soup and water (or milk).
Simmer until gravy thickens.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and add seasonings.
Cook until it thickens.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Add slightly beaten eggs. Add mashed bananas. Add chopped nuts, buttermilk and vanilla.

title: praline pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and condensed milk. Fold in whipped topping. Spread half of mixture in crust. Drizzle half the caramel topping. Sprinkle nuts and coconut. Repeat layers and freeze.

title: salsa
directions: Peel and cube the tomatoes.
Drain off all excess liquid from the tomatoes, onions and mangos.
Add remaining ingredients and boil about 1 hour.
Makes 25 pints.

title: slow cooker beef stroganoff
directions: Place the beef in the bottom of a slow cooker and season with salt and pepper to taste. Then add the onion, soup, mushrooms, chives and bouillon. In a separate small bowl, combine the flour, water, garlic and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well and add to the slow cooker. Cook on low setting for 7 to 8 hours. One hour before serving, stir in the sour cream and the parsley.

title: mom's tomato pudding
directions: Pour hot
water over tomatoes, then drop in cold water. Peel tomatoes
and
stew.
Add bread crumbs.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, margarine and lemon flavoring.

title: health drink
directions: Heat water to boil. Put cider and honey in water and stir. Drink 1/2 cup in the morning and 1/2 cup at bedtime. Lemon juice may be added.

title: santa fe salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve with fish or poultry.

title: blueberry grape salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple with juice.
Let congeal.
Whip cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread topping over congealed salad.

title: shrimp and crab garlic stir-fry
directions: Preheat wok frypan.
Saute 4 cloves of garlic in 1/8 pound of butter.
Saute seafood in another 1/8 pound of butter.
Precook pasta of your choice for 2 minutes.
Mix in with seafood and complete cooking.
Add salt to taste.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook about 5 minutes over meduim heat until limp.
Stir in the uncooked rice.
Saute about 2 minutes with vegetables.
Add salt, sugar, tomatoes (chopped up) and water.
Bring to a boil, then turn down to a simmer for 25 to 30 minutes, until rice is tender. Stir occasionally with fork.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven; add water and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer until tender.
Bone chicken; cut into bite-size pieces.
Bring broth to a boil; add pepper.
Combine flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; stir until ingredients are moistened.
Turn onto floured surface; knead (4 to 5 times).
Roll dough 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut in small square pieces.
Add to broth.
Reduce heat and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken, stirring after each addition.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in skillet with small amount of water until tender; drain. Cut into medium chunks. Place in bottom of 9x13 dish. Combine soups, sour cream, and milk. Add salt and pepper. Pour soup mixture over chicken top with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve over hot cooked rice or egg noodles.

title: zucchini bread or cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 large or 3 small greased loaf pans or 33 minutes in 15 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except poppy seed.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Fold in poppy seed.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, ungreased. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Insert toothpicks to test if done.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef very thin across the grain.
Brown and simmer until tender (1/2 hour to 1 1/2 hours).
Add sour cream, seasonings and mushrooms.
Heat.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: goblin cookies
directions: In a small saucepan or double boiler over low heat, melt chocolate, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal until well combined.
Spoon 1 tablespoon mixture into 15 (1 3/4-inch) paper baking cups.
Press down.
In a small bowl, combine peanut butter and applesauce.
Drop peanut butter mixture by teaspoons on top of chocolate.
Chill one hour or until firm; top each with one candy corn.
Makes 15.

title: arkansas rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 1 hour or until rice is tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: elegant cheese squares
directions: You will need a muffin pan, baking cups, icing decorations, cookie sheets, 1/2 gallon ice cream, nuts or sprinkle decorations and wax paper.

title: seven-up jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Add 7-Up. Let cool and thicken slightly.
Drain juice from canned pineapple and save.
Add marshmallows, pineapple (drained) and bananas to jello mixture.
Chill thoroughly until set.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, cornstarch and egg in a saucepan until thick.
While still hot, add room temperature cream cheese and butter.
Cool, then fold in Dream Whip.
Spread over jello and top with nuts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar in small bowl.
In larger bowl, mix together milk, vanilla instant pudding and Cool Whip.
Mix contents of both bowls together.
Layer with cookies, pudding, cookies, pudding, etc., ending with cookies on top.

title: spicy peanut chicken
directions: Combine chicken, salt and enough boiling water to cover in large skillet.
Return to boiling over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 18 to 20 minutes or just until tender. Remove to platter.
Cover half the chicken with foil and keep warm. Cool remaining half slightly; wrap and refrigerate for another meal.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Put in a crock pot.
Mix in cheese and salsa.
Cook on low.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients in mixer.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Roll into balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each cookie with 2 to 3 drops water.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: boeuf bourguignon
directions: Cut up the onion and bacon into small pieces and saute in an iron skillet in the butter until golden brown.
Remove the onion and bacon with a slotted spoon and place it in a large soup pot. Brown the beef cubes in the fat left from the bacon and onion.
As the individual cubes become brown, transfer them to the soup pot. When all the beef cubes are in the pot, sprinkle them with the flour.
Deglaze the iron skillet with the bouillon and add it and the wine to the pot.
Bind up the bouquet garni with string and place it in the pot.
Bring the mixture to a boil and simmer for two to three hours.
Taste and correct the seasoning with salt and pepper if desired.
Cut up and add the mushrooms and cook for one-half hour more.

title: one-half cup cake
directions: Mix as ingredients are given, putting the egg in after other ingredients are well mixed.
Bake at 350° until done, 20 minutes or more.

title: peach sauce
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, combine all sauce ingredients.
Cook until butter melts, stirring constantly. Serve warm or cool over pound cake, angel food cake or vanilla ice cream.

title: ribbon o' fudge bars
directions: In Dutch oven over low heat, melt marshmallows with butterscotch chips and butter, stirring until smooth.
Add popcorn; toss until well coated.
Press half of mixture firmly into greased 9-inch pan.
Spread fudge sauce evenly over mixture. Press remaining popcorn mixture over fudge.
Allow mixture to cool and harden.
Cut into bars.
Makes 16 bars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well; place in casserole dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and bake in pan of water for 2 hours at 325° to 350°.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In casserole dish layer chicken and vegetables.
Mix a can of broth with cream of mushroom soup, pour over vegetables and chicken.
Combine Bisquick and milk, pour over vegetables and chicken.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: squash dressing casserole
directions: Crumble cornbread into milk.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into prepared casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: small pound cake
directions: Note:
If using unsalted butter, you may want to add a dash of salt.

title: licking good salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let set until starts to congeal.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix other ingredients with whipped cream; fold with ingredients into gelatin.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: hazelnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat.
Stir in hazelnuts and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until dark.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter and sugars in large bowl until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, stirring until a soft dough forms.
Fold in nuts. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about 8 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: party crackers
directions: In paper sack (double), pour oyster crackers and all spices. Pour 1 cup of oil in bag.
Shake well.
Let set for 2 or 24 hours.

title: aunt jim's skillet cake pie
directions: Melt oleo in cast-iron skillet.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl. Add milk and blend until smooth.
Pour into melted oleo and don't stir.
Mix pie filling with water and pour onto middle of mixture in the skillet.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion pie
directions: Pour mixture over onion cheese mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees 1/2 hour or until custard sets.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer beef first, potatoes next and onions last.
Mix soup and water and pour over other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Remove cover.
Spread cheese on top.
Return to oven and cook just long enough to melt cheese.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: In a pot, put butter, then put marshmallows.
Then put 12 small Milky Ways in.
When all melts, add Rice Krispies.
Stir until all coated.

title: mama's caramel pie
directions: Divide sugar.
Mix egg yolks, cornstarch or flour and milk and half of sugar.
Heat, but not to boiling.
Brown other half of sugar and pour in small stream into milk and egg mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake in slow oven until brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain. In 9 x 13 casserole dish, layer potatoes. Slice onion on top of potatoes. Add corn. Layer the browned sausage on top. Pour tomato sauce over the sausage. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks, gradually add milk and cook over low heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Custard will be thick enough to spread over layered cookies and sliced bananas. Layer continuously (this makes a large banana pudding).

title: easy pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Line jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
Spray with Pam.
Spread batter in pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle a cloth generously with powdered sugar.
Invert cake onto cloth and roll up.
Let cool.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until clear.
Add jello and cool.
Pour over fruit in baked pie shell.
Refrigerate immediately.
Cool for 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: baklava
directions: Boil all together till medium syrup, about half hour.
Set aside and cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Keep cheese at room temperature and mix up with hands.
Add 1/2 cup nuts, parsley, Worcestershire and onions.
Mix thoroughly and let stand in refrigerator until firm, then roll into ball and roll entire ball in mixture of remaining nuts and parsley.
Press onto snack crackers.

title: old-fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Stir constantly until small amount forms a hard ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour evenly over 4 quarts unsalted, popped corn.
Mix well.
Form quickly into medium sized balls, using buttered hands.
Makes 12.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes. Stir now and then.
Uncover; cook until sauce thickens.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve over rice.

title: crab meat
directions: Blend all of the ingredients, except the crab.
Fold in crab meat.
Spread on each half of English muffin.
Freeze.
When ready to use, bake at 500° for 5 minutes.
Cut into fourths to serve.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add celery and green onions.
Mix gelatin with 1/4 cup water.
Add to soup mix.
Add shrimp and mayonnaise.
Spray Pam in shrimp mold.
Pour mix into pan.
Chill several hours or overnight.
To remove mold from pan, put bottom of pan in warm water about 30 seconds to loosen.
Flip over onto serving tray and tap gently.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into a ball.
Roll ball in finely chopped nuts or garnish any way you desire.

title: basic roll dough
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle or crumble yeast into water.
Let stand until dissolved.
Stir.
Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Add about half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in additional flour.
Turn out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead.
Place in a greased bowl and brush top lightly with shortening.
Cover and let rise in a warm place free from draft until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and shape into rolls.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes depending on shape of roll.

title: enola's oriental cornish hens
directions: Sprinkle inside of hens with salt.
Tuck legs.
Place in a microwave dish, cover with plastic wrap and microwave at half power for 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Brush hens with sauce; grill about 20 minutes, brushing with sauce several times.

title: chunky italian soup
directions: Cook beef and onion in a Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink; drain.
Return mixture to pan. Stir in tomatoes, next 7 ingredients and chili powder; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes. Stir in green beans or kidney beans, carrot and zucchini.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Stir in pasta.
Sprinkle each serving with cheese.
Yield: 10 cups.

title: south of the border shrimp platter
directions: Fill medium bowl half full with crushed ice.
Arrange shrimp on ice.
Place bowl in center of large platter.
Place salsa and guacamole dip in small bowls at each end of platter.
Fill remaining area on platter with tortilla chips.
Makes 16 servings.

title: my aunt dina's cookies
directions: Mix eggs, 2 cups of sugar, butter, vanilla and flour in a bowl.
On the side, mix 1/2 cup flour and baking soda; add to cookie mix.
Mixture will be semi-moist.
Preheat oven to 350°. Roll dough into small balls (about size of superball) and place on cookie sheet.
Cook in oven about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies are ready when bottom is golden brown.
Cool on rack.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef, pork, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, 2 teaspoons salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, egg and milk; mix thoroughly. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonful into balls.
In a large skillet, slowly brown and cook meatballs in oil.
Remove meatballs and keep warm.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: In large plastic bag or bowl, place part of the chunked potatoes.
Give them a light spray.
Add more potatoes; spray again and continue until all potatoes are prepared.
Dump soup mix on them and toss or shake until evenly coated.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes, until potatoes are tender in 13 x 9-inch pan in a 450° oven.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients (except corn meal). Add corn meal and gradually beat buttermilk into mixture. Batter will be stiff. Melt lard in frying pan. When smoking hot, drop in batter by spoonful and cook 3 minutes on each side.

title: lassi
directions: Mix together carefully in the blender so as not to damage it with the ice.
Serve while still frothy.
Garnish with a sprig of fresh mint for a healthy and refreshing drink East Indian style.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook the chicken, skin and
cut
up the meat.
Save the skin. Meat the meat with
the
broth,
crumbs and eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place
in a baking dish.
Grind the skin and cover the mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and sifted dry ingredients, butter and corn.
Beat until well mixed.
Drop by spoonful into a hot, deep fryer.
Fry for 3 to 4 minutes, until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with warm maple syrup.
Makes 18 large or 24 small fritters.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs well; add pineapple and carrots.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla last.
Beat well.
Bake in a large pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Check middle with clean knife and continue baking if necessary until knife comes out clean.

title: spicy pear relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium nonaluminum saucepan.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm or at room temperature with pork.
Yields 2 cups (16 calories and 6% fat per tablespoon). Protein 0.1, fat 0.1 (saturated fat 0), carbohydrate 4.2, fiber 0.5, cholesterol 0, sodium 9.

title: brownies
directions: Turn oven on to 350°.
In large bowl, combine everything, but nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate chips. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: nanny's gingerbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs.
Beat well; add molasses.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cheese with sugar; mix lemon jello with cup of water and add lemon juice and let cool.
Whip Pet milk to peaks.
Blend in lemon jello with the cheese; blend in with Pet milk.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions on package.
Mix the soups and broth; set aside.
Layer chicken and rice, also mushrooms (optional), in oblong casserole dish.
Pour the broth and soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: quick mushroom sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir together soup and sour cream.
Heat through over low heat, but do not boil.
Serve with vegetables, beef or burgers.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: frozen cucumber salad
directions: Combine vegetables; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain dry.
Combine sugar, vinegar and seasoning.
When sugar is dissolved, pour over drained vegetables.
Spoon in plastic containers.

title: egg nog(1 serving)
directions: Place all ingredients in electric blender.
Mix for 1 minute. Garnish with nutmeg.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; then add sifted dry ingredients.
Add carrots.
Mix.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add nuts last.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Pick chicken off bone.
Mix together the Ro-Tel, mushroom soup, chicken soup, 2 tablespoons of sour cream and chicken.
Line baking dish with Doritos chips.
Place chicken mixture over chips.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted on top.
Can cook in microwave or oven.
May add additional chips, if desired.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets in boiling salt water until tender. Put in colander to drain and cool.
When cool, peel and slice. Set aside.
Meanwhile, fry bacon in heavy iron skillet.
When the pieces are browned, remove from the skillet and place on paper toweling to drain.

title: hummus(dip)
directions: Combine garlic and drained chickpeas (reserve liquid) in food processor.
Add olive oil, lemon juice, tahini paste and paprika. Process until mixture is smooth.
Beat in sufficient liquid from chickpeas until consistency of sour cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with pita wedges, crackers or fresh vegetable "dippers".

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: western burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 can French fried onions, 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce and mustard; mix well. Form into 4 burgers; broil or grill to desired doneness, turning carefully.
Top with bacon, remaining sauce and onions.
Broil for 30 seconds, or until onions are golden.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all together. Can either bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (until cheese is melted) or have a function to go to put in crock-pot and plug in on low for about 4 hours or until cheese is melted and eat away with chips.

title: baked flounder almondine(microwave)
directions: Arrange fish in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Add seasonings, lemon juice and margarine.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Vent 1 corner by turning back plastic wrap slightly.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes on High.
Fish should flake easily.
Garnish with almonds.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 10-inch ungreased pie pan. Bake 40 minutes at 375°. Pie forms a crust on the bottom.

title: red lobster cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix Bisquick, water and cheese. Drop by large spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake for 8-10 minutes. After baking, (while hot) brush on melted butter or margarine mixed with garlic powder, parsley flakes and Italian seasoning. Serve hot.

title: oriental salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator.

title: cinnamon puffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 nutmeg.
In separate bowl, combine shortening, 1/2 sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to this.
Then stir in milk until smooth.
Line muffin cups with paper liners.
Fill 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes for large (12), less time for small (24).
Melt margarine.
Mix remaining 1/2 sugar, remaining 1/2 nutmeg and cinnamon.
While still warm, dip in melted margarine and roll in sugar mixture.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and finely chop vegetables.
Stir in Ranch dressing.

title: luscious pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and cloves. Beat together sugar, oil and eggs until light and fluffy. Add pumpkin and blend well. Add dry ingredients alternately to pumpkin mixture with water, beating well after each addition. Pour batter into greased pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Cool on rack. Makes two 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans, 1 (9 x 13) or 2 Bundt pans.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: In a 4-quart pan, saute onion, celery and garlic in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add beans, pepper and taco seasoning.
Stir in chicken broth and water.
Bring to a boil and lower heat. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: grandma gerardi's broccoli pasta
directions: Chop broccoli flowerets.
Skin stalk and chop.
Cook with 1 pound pasta until tender (pasta).
Drain.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O and pudding together dry!
Add pineapple and juice. Fold in Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
It is better if it stands for a couple of hours.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix dates, boiling water and soda and let stand.
Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, cocoa and salt to sugar mixture alternately with date mixture.
Spread dough out in a large cookie sheet with sides.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: sour cream-popcorn meal cornbread
directions: Beat eggs, milk, shortening and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Grease a square cake pan with shortening and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers to desired thickness, 1/4 to 1/2-inches.
Let stand in lime water for 24 hours.
Drain and soak in fresh water for 4 hours.
Change water every hour.
Take out and drain.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and lemon or orange peel.
Beat in dry ingredients just until combined.
Divide dough in half.
Wrap tightly and refrigerate 4 hour or overnight.

title: mom's apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and Mandarin oranges.
Chop walnuts. Slice red apples into small bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in medium mixing bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until use.

title: spiced carrots
directions: Bring to boil top seven ingredients.
Lower heat and cook until peppers and onions are tender.
Pour over cooked carrots (will cover up to 2 pounds).
Refrigerate.

title: mounds chocolate wacky cake
directions: Mix together the first 9 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in an 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt.
Chill until it begins to thicken. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with half of torn cake pieces.
Pour over this 1/2 of strawberries and cream mixture another layer of cake, then rest of mixture.
Chill 4 to 5 hours.

title: pineapple-cranberry mold
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Heat to boiling and pour over gelatin. Stir until completely dissolved. Stir in pineapple and remaining ingredients in order given. Turn into 8-inch ring mold. Chill until firm.

title: sally skok's rice cake
directions: Cook two cups rice in 5 cups salted water (1 tablespoon salt) until all water is absorbed.
Add the butter and cream cheese and stir until dissolved.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown and drain beef.
Stir in 3/4 c. sauce, 1 c. cheese, and veggies.
Spoon filling onto tortillas and roll.
Place in 13 x 9 pan, seam side down.
Spoon remaining sauce and cheese over the top.
Bake for 15-20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sherry pardue's beef noodles
directions: Cook noodles following directions on the package.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; mix mushroom soup in skillet with ground beef and onion.
Put one layer of ground beef, onion and soup in baking dish and layer with noodle mixture.
Place Swiss cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is brown, about 5 minutes at 325°.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut bread dough into marshmallow size pieces and put in pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Top with sauce made of pudding, brown sugar, butter and cream heated on stove long enough to mix together and melt butter.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and flip pan over so that sauce can cover rolls.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Melt butter and add water and brown sugar.
Pour into the bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Add pecan pieces to sugar mixture, if desired, and then lay in the rolls.
Do not crowd, as rolls must rise again, doubling size.
Place in warm area, covered with towel, and allow to rise.
Bake in 400° oven for approximately 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Allow to cool slightly in pan and then flip out onto wax paper lined dish.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers with 1 1/2 sticks melted margarine.
Press into large dish.
Mix confectioners sugar, 1 stick unmelted margarine, milk and vanilla; spread over crust.
Place cut-up bananas on top of sugar mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.

title: hardtack candy
directions: Combine sugar, white Karo and water and cook to 310°.
Then add flavoring and coloring.
Pour out onto powdered sugar.
When rock hard, break into pieces.

title: dusty millers
directions: Make into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: green onion quiche
directions: Line pie or quiche dish with pastry and prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Gently prick again with fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese in pastry.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp and bacon shish-cabobs
directions: Wrap peeled shrimp in bacon.
Slip bacon and shrimp on skewers, followed by pineapple and mushrooms.
Repeat and barbecue! Pour pineapple juice on top!
Enjoy!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, Karo and water in large pan.
Cook until hard ball stage.
Add peanuts and butter.
Cook until syrup turns golden brown or until peanuts are golden brown, stirring constantly. Remove from fire.
Add vanilla; stir, then add soda.
Stir until mixture foams.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let brittle cool.
Break in pieces and store in airtight container.

title: hash brown egg casserole
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with hash browns.
Brown the meat, layer the remaining recipe.
Beat the eggs and half and half or Carnation.
Pour over.
Bake one hour at 350° or until done. This can be done the night before and refrigerated, then add your eggs when ready to bake.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Place biscuits in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over that place browned hamburger, then Ragu sauce, then Velveeta cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, melted butter and syrup. Add pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°. (Double recipe makes 3 pies.)

title: corn crab chowder
directions: Saute garlic, onion, butter and cayenne pepper in butter.
In a small saucepan, place corn, cream cheese, potato soup and milk; stir over low heat (do not boil).
Add crab meat and simmer about 10 minutes uncovered.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain.
Bring to a boil 2 cups of water and rice.
Combine all ingredients with rice; let cook until rice is done.
Add more water as needed.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Chop all vegetables except carrots.
Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine eggs, oil, milk and sugar. Add vanilla, almond flavoring and butter flavoring.
Add sifted flour, salt, baking powder and poppy seed.
Pour into muffin tins and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients except butter. Coat hot pan with butter.
Pour remaining butter into batter and mix. Pour by spoonful into pan. Raise pan to run batter around pan in thin layer.
Cooks very quickly.

title: fresh peach bread
directions: Cream margarine and 1 cup of sugar.
Add eggs and buttermilk. Beat.
Sift 2 cups of flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in peaches and lemon flavoring.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar, 3 tablespoons of flour and cinnamon and cut in butter.
Sprinkle over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Split breasts; salt and pepper and dip in melted butter.
Mix rice and soup.
Spread soup mixture in a large, shallow buttered casserole dish.
Top with chicken and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: lemonade ice cream pie
directions: With electric mixer, blend soft ice cream and lemonade until thoroughly mixed. Pour into crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.
Decorate with fresh strawberries or sprigs of mint.

title: strawberry-lemon pie
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and milk in a saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring until gelatin and sugar dissolve.
Add lemon rind and juice.
Let mixture cool to room temperature. Refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes until chilled.
In a separate bowl, whip the cream to stiff-peak stage.
Fold in chilled gelatin mixture and pour into pie shell.
Spread berries evenly over top of pie.
Refrigerate for several hours until firm.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix milk, sugar, vinegar, egg, margarine, cornstarch, salt, celery seed and mustard. Cook until thick. Set aside. Mix potatoes, eggs, onions and mayonnaise. Add cooked ingredients and mix well.

title: sesame wafers
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add water/oil combination and mix as for pie crust.
Knead in bowl until smooth.
Divide into two parts and knead again.
Roll out to 1/8-inch or less in thickness directly onto cookie sheet.
Mark into desired shape and prick with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour or until crackers are slightly brown and crisp.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and chill for several hours or overnight. Good with raw vegetables or on baked potatoes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all-cook 15 to 20 minutes or until brown in 400 degree oven. Use long casserole dish-a little smaller than 9 x 13.

title: large batch of spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds and cook as directed on package. Drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Add all ingredients and mix well.

title: microwaved cheesy grits
directions: Combine the water and grits in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with lid or heavy plastic wrap and microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir, turn and microwave 4 more minutes.
Add cheese (cut into small pieces) and other ingredients.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds; stir, then cook an additional 30 seconds.
Let stand 1 minute; sprinkle paprika on top.
Yields 4 servings, containing 135 calories per serving.

title: pennies from heaven
directions: Cook carrot slices until tender (not mushy).
Mix rest of ingredients, pour over carrot slices, after drained well. Refrigerate 6 hours or more before serving.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Dip lime sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale slowly over sherbet until punch bowl is filled.
Add more sherbet and ginger ale as needed.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Pour in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 to 60 minutes.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Mix and pour in a skillet.
Pat down.
Cook over low heat, about 30 minutes.
Do not peek or remove lid.
Yields 4 servings.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk, and sugar in large bowl with whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour cold milk into bowl.
Add pumpkin, pudding mixes, and spices.
Beat with whisk until mixed.
Will be thick. Spread over cream cheese.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: mostaccioli
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, stir tomato paste, spices and water
until
well	blended.
Bring
to
a	boil.
Add raw ground beef in
small
bits
and
blend with a fork.
Then add thinly sliced
pepperoni.	Simmer	for 3 hours, stirring occasionally, uncovered.	After
hours,
boil mostaccioli pasta as directed on package in
a
separate pot.
In 2 medium size casserole dishes, layer
pasta,
sauce
and sprinkle with cheese 2 times.
Serve
immediately with hot, garlic bread and salad. Serves 12.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Stir together the breadcrumbs, cocoa and chopped nuts; set mixture aside.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, beating well for 1 minute.
Stir in milk, vanilla, salt and breadcrumb mixture. Pour into a lightly greased 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or crock-pot on low heat for 5 to 6 hours.
Sausage can be substituted for bacon.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter in a small pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Make small balls out of dough (walnut size).
Roll balls in butter or oleo.
Then roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in well-greased angel food cake pan.
Let rise until pan is full, about 1 hour in warm place.
Put in oven at 350° for about 25 minutes and then cover with foil and bake until golden brown. Dump on plate.
Pull apart as you eat it.

title: cracker jack ii
directions: Boil to
a hard ball stage, then add 1/2 cup butter or margarine and 1
teaspoon
soda, dissolved in a little water, after removing from heat.
Pour over popped corn.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Crumble graham crackers in mixing bowl.
Mix peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar in bowl.
Melt chocolate in saucepan and pour over mixture.
Let chill overnight and serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery until slightly soft.
Add broccoli, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add rice, cheese and soup.
Blend well and pour into a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 100 year old cookie
directions: Cream together sugar and lard.
Add eggs and beat hard.
Place soda in a cup and add a mite of water until it foams up.
Sift flour and add to mixture.
Mix smoothly and swiftly, then neatly roll out on a board.
If too soft, add a little flour.
Cut out and bake in a hot oven.

title: andy jackson's watermelon pickles
directions: Peel rinds of watermelon.
Trim off every trace of green outer skin and pink fruit.
Cut white rind into small 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Place cut rinds in bottom of a large earthen dish. Sprinkle lightly and evenly with salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach well; add soup, cream cheese and 1/2 the onion rings.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle remaining onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: On flour tortilla, spread cream cheese thinly. Put a layer of Carl Buddig meat, then another layer of cream cheese. Roll and cut into slices.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine.
Add orange peel and juice.
Add eggs.
Mix. Add cranberries, walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cake topping
directions: Thaw container of Cool Whip.
Make pudding according to box directions.
Fold pudding and Cool Whip together.
Add crushed pineapple.
Use over slices of yellow cake or angel food cake.

title: string beans with tomatoes(from 1975 edition)
directions: In pan, melt butter; add onion and saute.
Pour in juice from tomatoes and simmer a few minutes.
Mash tomatoes and add to onion and juice.
Add the sugar.
Cook frozen string beans and drain. Add to first mixture.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Mix and cook another 5 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well with fork and add sugar, oil and flavoring. Blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift in dry ingredients; blend until creamed.
Bake in 2 floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour (glass pans 325°).

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll between two wax paper sheets. Lift top layer of waxed paper, turn into pie plate and lift other piece of wax paper from crust.
Prick pie crust with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° until browned.

title: chocolate drink
directions: Mix all of the contents in a blender for about 30 seconds. Refrigerate until cool.

title: refreshing applesauce jello
directions: Heat applesauce and dry Jell-O in saucepan on medium heat just until bubbly. Add 7-Up and stir until it stops foaming. Refrigerate until firm.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter 10 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, add flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Beat 1 minute. Fold in coconut and flavoring.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Add soda to boiling water and cool. Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and soda mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well (this takes a very large pan for mixing).
Keep mixture in tight container in refrigerator.
Let set at least 8 hours before using from it.
May be kept for 6 weeks.
After refrigerating, do not stir again.
Spoon into muffin tins and bake 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
This makes about 3 quarts.

title: grandma's good cookies
directions: Beat sugars, oil, oleo, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, then Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: tossed salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix together sugar, dry mustard, 2 teaspoons salt and vinegar. Add onion juice, vegetable oil and poppy seed slowly, whisking constantly, until thick.
Refrigerate until ready for use.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix chili sauce, grape jelly and mustard in crock-pot.
Mix remaining ingredients and form into meatballs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, then put in crock-pot and simmer for 6 to 10 hours.
(The longer they simmer, the better they taste.)

title: oatmeal nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into pie shells. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into dish and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo dirt
directions: Crush cookies in a blender or food processor to a fine cookie dust.
Set aside (this is the dirt).

title: smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Cover to top with crushed ice.
Blend thoroughly.
Serve in a tall glass.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate surprise(very good candy)
directions: Combine Krispies, sugar, peanut butter and margarine.
Mix well.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Melt chips, Hershey bar and wax in double boiler.
Dip balls.
Place on wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: special k loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover during first 30 minutes, then uncover to brown.

title: angel food bavarian with strawberries
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces in 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan. Soak package of plain gelatin in 1/4 c. cold water. Add 1/2 c. boiling water. Cool. Add juice of 1 lemon, 1 c. orange juice, and 1 c. sugar. Let set until mixture congeals. Whip 1/2 pint of whipping cream and fold into jello mixture. Pour over angel food cake. Pat down. Chill in refrigerator about 3 hours or over night. Top with strawberries.

title: taco soup
directions: Fry onion and hamburger; drain.
Add corn, garbanzo beans, red kidney beans, black beans, sliced black olives and diced tomatoes; do not drain juices.
Put in crock-pot.
Add taco seasoning, cumin and pepper.
Simmer on low until hot.
Serve topped with grated Cheddar cheese, crushed corn chips and a dab of sour cream (optional).

title: oriental green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Layer casserole with ingredients; spread out mushroom soup on top.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes. Add onion rings and continue to bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate swirl coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Stir together the coconut, nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon melted butter; set aside.
Mix the baking mix, 1/4 cup sugar, remaining melted butter, egg and milk.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds; pour into pan.
Spoon chocolate over batter.
With knife, cut through batter several times for marbled effect.
Sprinkle coconut mixture evenly over top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onions, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic; saute lightly.
Stir in broth, uncooked rice, okra, chicken, salt, basil, thyme and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, or until rice is tender.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Stir into soup.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes, or until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
If desired, serve over cooked rice.

title: sauce a rachid (peanut butter chicken)
directions: Soften peanut butter in deep pan.
Add tomatoes and hot sauce to taste.
In another pan, brown chicken pieces.
Drain and set aside.
Using same oil, brown vegetables.
Drain.
Add chicken and vegetables to sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Refrigerate until needed for serving.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: brownies
