directions: First heat about 1/4 cup of the oil with chocolate squares until melted.
Cool mixture.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add vanilla and cooled oil and chocolate mixture. Beat until well blended.
Add dry ingredients alternately with remaining oil.
Mix well.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Shred or dice bread.
Chop onion and celery and saute in butter until soft.
Pour over bread.
Add 1/2 cup soup (not diluted) and seasonings.
Mix well; form into balls.
Put into casserole dish.

title: beverly's blender egg custard pie
directions: In blender, put sugar, eggs, vanilla, nutmeg and enough milk to fill blender to 1 1/2-inch from top.
Mix for 30 seconds or until blended.
Pour into 2 deep pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave pies in oven to cool down. Perfect every time.

title: baked parmesan cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a large frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning until browned, about 10 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Add cream cheese and Jell-O mix. Add remaining ingredients; blend and chill in 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: turkey country steak
directions: Place oil in skillet and saute onion and bell pepper until tender and lightly brown.
Place in bowl and mix together with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 4 steak patties and cook on grill until done or place steaks in Pam sprayed pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° until done.
May need to turn steaks over once. When steaks are almost done, uncover so steaks will brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken cutlets with olive sauce
directions: Pound chicken between sheets of wax paper or Saran Wrap, until about 1/4-inch thick.
Coat with flour, shaking off excess.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute chicken 4 minutes on each side until lightly browned and cooked through.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add shallot and saute 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in gravy, olives, capers, vinegar and Tabasco.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with water; add to the skillet. Cook, stirring, until the sauce boils and thickens.
Simmer 1 minute.
Serve over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: pecan and date rolls
directions: Mix sugar and milk and bring to boiling point.
Add dates and cherries and boil slowly until mixture forms soft balls in water; add butter.
Sit in cold water.
When cool, beat until it thickens; add nuts and place in damp cloth and roll.
Let it sit overnight.
Slice.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix well; form into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dad's swiss steak
directions: Cut Steak into individual pieces.
Salt and Pepper the meat. Place Carrots on the bottom of large Crock Pot.
Add meat.
Add all remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well and pour into crock pot and cover.
Cook on high for 8 - 10 hours.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Slice strawberries and mix with glaze; set aside.
Mix Dream Whip and cream cheese with milk with mixer until smooth.
Add cake, crumbled and mix well.
Put 1/2 glaze mixture in large baking dish.
Add all of angel food cake mixture.
Top with remaining glaze.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: fruit and vegetable toss
directions: Combine lettuce, cheese and celery in large salad bowl.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add herb stuffing.
Blend and set aside.
Steam squash, onion and sugar together for 5 minutes only. Drain.
Add soup and sour cream.
Blend together.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with 2/3 of the stuffing mixture.
Pour squash mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining 1/3 of stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush the cookies and mix with the melted butter. Reserve 1 cup cookies for topping.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the ice cream layer on next and freeze until firm.

title: grandma arnold's christmas card cookies
directions: Cream butter and stir in sugar and molasses.
Stir in coffee. Add remaining ingredients and stir until a soft dough is formed. Turn dough out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Wrap dough and chill for 2 hours.
Shape dough as desired and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool and decorate.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen, depending on shape and size.

title: swiss steak
directions: In cooking oil, brown meat on both sides.
Place slices of onion on top of meat.
Add canned tomato, seasoned salt and garlic salt.
Simmer for a little over an hour.
Cook rice in last half hour.
Serve swiss steak over rice.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp and feta cheese
directions: Saute shrimp and pepper flakes in 2 tablespoons olive oil for 1 to 2 minutes (until slightly pink).
Arrange shrimp in 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish; sprinkle with Feta cheese.
Add remaining oil to skillet; saute garlic over low heat.
Add tomato wedges; cook 1 minute and stir in wine and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon over shrimp.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spoon over cooked pasta.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients except eggs and beat with electric mixer until smooth. Beat eggs and add to mixture. Pour into pie crust and bake 40 minutes until center is almost set. Cool on rack. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: orange bread
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, orange peel, orange extract and milk; beat well.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder; add to batter and stir until moistened.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Best second day; freezes well.

title: diabetic apple cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chopped apples in medium bowl. Drain cherries, saving juice.
Add cherries to apples; set aside. In small saucepan, combine cherry juice, concentrate and 1/4 cup fructose. Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add almond flavoring.
Pour over fruit.
Pour entire fruit mixture into a round 2-quart casserole dish which has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Combine flour, oats, cinnamon, margarine, 1/4 cup apple juice concentrate and 2 tablespoons fructose, mixing to a crumb-like consistency.
Crumble over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned.
Yields 16 servings.
Each serving contains 141 calories (27% from fat).

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and add eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and cocoa.
Alternate flour mixture and milk.
Add vanilla. Start with flour and end with flour.
Leave cocoa out for yellow cake.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 large layers.

title: audrey's mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine Cool Whip and pie filling. Stir in crushed pineapple and set aside.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil and place in a Dutch oven.
In skillet, combine remaining ingredients and stir until smooth, adding enough water to make enough sauce to completely cover chicken.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato donuts
directions: Let first 3 ingredients rise for about 1 hour.
After mixing, add the remaining ingredients.
Add enough flour to stiffen dough and keep from sticking to hands, approximately 5 to 6 cups.
Let rise until dough doubles in size, for about 1 hour.
Roll and cut 1/2-inch thick.
Fry in hot fat.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg.
Put on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and 10x sugar.
Spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare chocolate cake mix according to package directions for cupcakes.
In a separate bowl, cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Into this mixture, beat in the egg, then stir in chocolate chips.
Line cupcake tins with cupcake liners and fill 2/3 full with chocolate cake batter.
Add 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture to the center; top with more cake mix.
Bake according to directions for cupcakes.
Cool and frost with chocolate or cream cheese frosting.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: date nut bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add seasonings.
Use part of flour to coat nuts and dates.
Add rest of flour to mix, continue beating well. Add fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in wax paper lined pan (7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inches) for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift the flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in oleo until well mixed with first ingredients, then add milk.
Knead several times.
Roll out on lightly floured board until about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or inverted glass or drop by spoonfuls.
Place on heavy-duty aluminum foil or cookie sheet which has been well-greased.
Bake until browned, approximately 13 to 14 minutes.
Yields 16 biscuits.

title: american luncheon salad cranberry and seafood layers
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water over hot water.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil the syrup, water and sugar together until it spins a thread
or the mixture registers 240° on thermometer.
Pour slowly a
drop
at a time, first over the egg white which has been beaten stiff, but not dry.
Beat rapidly until all syrup is added.
Stir
in vanilla and add nuts.
Beat until mixture stands alone.
Drop
by teaspoon on wax paper and let dry.
I always put a half pecan on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts.
Combine all other ingredients and mix well.
Form into a ball and roll in reserved nuts.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: dry bread crumbs
directions: Cut in 1/2-inch cubes.
Microwave in 3-quart casserole for 6 to 7 minutes, or until dry, stirring after 3 minutes.
Crush in blender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Cream all but teaspoon of the margarine with 2 tablespoons tarragon and salt and pepper.
Place chicken in baking dish and spread the herb mix over it.
Add the onion.
Bake at 375° until done, about 45 minutes.
Remove the chicken.
Place on a serving dish and keep warm.

title: cream puffs
directions: In saucepan, heat water, butter and salt to full rolling boil. Reduce heat; quickly stir in flour, mixing vigorously with wooden spoon until mixture leaves the sides of the pan in a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs in 6 additions, beating after each addition until mixture is very smooth.
(An electric mixer at a low speed makes this procedure easier.)
Level off 1 1/4 teaspoon dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Using this amount as a guide for size, drop remaining dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven (400°) for about 20 minutes (will be light brown on bottom).
Fill with favorite spread.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: eggplant with mein see and hoisin
directions: Cut pork into julienne strips.
Marinate pork in cornstarch, soy sauce and sherry. Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch cubes. Sprinkle with salt and set aside for 20 minutes, then drain and pat dry. Stir-fry pork and set aside.
Stir-fry garlic in oil until fragrant.
Add eggplant and stir-fry until tender (not soggy). Add sesame oil, chili garlic sauce, mein see, hoisin, sugar and pork. Stir-fry until hot through. Garnish with cilantro.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl sift together sugar, flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add oats and raisins. In smaller bowl beat together (with mixer) eggs, oil, milk and vanilla.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and blend well with spoon.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bottoms of cookies are light golden brown.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Crush 1 cup of berries and cook with water for 2 minutes. Sieve.
Blend sugar and cornstarch; stir in berry juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until glaze is thick and clear.

title: sweet crisp pickles
directions: Drain juice from jar of dill pickles and drain pickles on paper towels.
Slice pickles (quartered) longwise.
Place layer of pickles, then layer of sugar alternating pimentos, garlic and hot pepper (if desired).
Keep alternating until you use up all pickles, sugar, garlic and pimentos.
Turn jar end to end occasionally (with lid on) until all sugar is dissolved.
Must use all sugar.
Shake jar occasionally to help dissolve.
Refrigerate to keep indefinitely.

title: rolled white cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add 4 cups flour, baking powder, soda and salt; mix well.
Add remainder of flour by cupfuls until dough does not stick to finger.

title: polynesian pot roast
directions: Brown meat in oil in large Dutch oven on all sides.
Add chopped onion and saute.
Combine in mixing bowl the pineapple, brown sugar, ginger, vinegar, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce and stir thoroughly.
Pour over meat along with beef bouillon broth and bring to boil.
Cover and lower heat.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours. Potatoes and carrots may be added and cooked for last hour.
Remove meat and vegetables and thicken gravy with cornstarch.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Put apples in to almost the top. Sprinkle mixture of remaining ingredients on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package except bake 20 minutes. Beat vanilla, egg, milk and cream cheese in a large bowl until smooth.
Pour over baked brownie layer. Bake until topping is set, 25 minutes.
Cool 2 hours. Spread with pie filling.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch or 2-inch squares. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 small or 24 large brownies.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch strips.
Mix salt, pepper, garlic, paprika and Worcestershire with flour.
Coat steak.
Put oil into a large pot.
Brown steak on both sides.
Add milk, bell pepper and onion.
Let cook on low about 1 hour, stirring often.
Cook rice according to package.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients together.
Put 3 tortillas in bottom of baking dish.
Put hamburger mixture over this and cover with sliced cheese.
Rotate until tortillas are gone.
Pour cream of chicken soup with one can of water, heated, over this.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Mix bran flakes, milk and sugar in another bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and applesauce. Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Spoon batter into muffin cups 2/3 full and bake for 18 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon puff
directions: Combine eggs, milk and mushroom soup.
Stir well, then blend in remaining ingredients and stir well.
Place in a buttered casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
When ready to serve, have Cheddar cheese soup hot and put a dab or more on top of Salmon Puff.

title: special green beans
directions: Place alternate layers of beans and onions in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, pepper, salt, mushrooms and mushroom liquid with almonds.
Pour over bean and onion mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: pecan popovers
directions: Put eggs in blender and blend 2 seconds.
Add flour and salt and blend 10 seconds.
Stir in pecans.
Grease large muffin tins and fill 1/2 full.
Bake in 475° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until brown and firm.
A few minutes before removing from oven, prick each popover with fork to let steam escape.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and Wesson oil over hot water.
Beat in remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 14 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and cut into squares.
They may be iced with a chocolate icing.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, eggs, margarine, vanilla and milk. Place in a greased casserole dish.

title: wayne's favorite squash lasagna
directions: Cook together the first 7 ingredients.
Add rice.
Boil the zucchini.
Mix the egg and cottage cheese.
Put mix on top of squash, then put egg/cheese over that and layer.
Put grated cheese on very top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Note: Mix is the first 9 ingredients.

title: walnut oat pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first nine ingredients; mix well.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: gram's white chili
directions: Combine beans (drained), chicken broth, 1/2 of the onions and garlic in large pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer until beans are very soft.
Add more broth if necessary. Saute remaining onions in oil until tender. Add chilies and seasonings; mix thoroughly. Add to bean mixture. Add chicken and simmer 1 hour.
Serve with cheese and cornbread or chips.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Soften the gelatin in the cold water in a large mixing bowl. Stir in the boiling water and whisk the mixture slowly until gelatin dissolves.
Cool to room temperature.
Whisk in the mayonnaise, lemon juice, grated onion, Tabasco, paprika, salt and dill.
Stir to blend completely and refrigerate for about 20 minutes or until the mixture begins to thicken slightly.

title: banana burrito
directions: Add all ingredients into flour tortilla; roll up and put into microwave until hot.

title: sunshine ice cream pie
directions: Spoon alternate layers of ice cream and sherbet into crust. Freeze at least 3 hours or overnight.
To serve, spread whipped topping decoratively on pie.
Top with orange segments and coconut.
Decorate with sprig of mint, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: country-fried steak
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup flour.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 4 x 4-inch pieces.
Cook in hot fat until browned.
Remove, add remaining flour and brown. Add milk and salt; cook until thick.

title: torn tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in skillet; saute onions. Add next 4 ingredients; remove from heat.
Beat eggs; add cream and stir into tomato mixture.
Cover bottom of a 2-quart casserole with half the sauce and half the cubed cheese.
Repeat layers until all tortillas, sauce and cubed cheese are gone.
Top with sour cream, paprika and chopped cilantro; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chill-out spinach salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine all ingredients, except dressing. Add dressing and toss lightly.
Serve at once.

title: fried turkey
directions: Rub on turkey the night before.
Wrap the turkey in foil.
Use one per turkey.
Fry turkey in oil that has covered the turkey. Fry turkey 5 1/2 minutes per pound.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix ingredients adding water sparingly.
(Batter should not be runny.)

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion; combine all. Put together with the rice and bake until puffed up and rice is done, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake covered. Open the last 15 minutes to brown some. Bake at 350°. Add liquid if needed.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, layer the pan in the order given.
Top with black olives, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/4 cup juice. Combine vinegar, sugar and beet juice. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Pour liquid over beets and store in the refrigerator.

title: pork chop hot pot
directions: Brown chops well in a frypan over medium heat.
Arrange in bottom of baking dish or casserole.
Cover with peeled sliced potatoes, then the onion rings.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour the broth over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover.
Place apple quarters on top of contents of baking dish. Dust the apples with cinnamon.
Cover and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: gala crab salad
directions: In a bowl, combine rice, crab, salad dressing, green pepper, onion and celery.
Pack into an oiled 6-cup mold.
Chill at least 6 hours or overnight.
Unmold onto a bed of lettuce.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press into an ungreased 10
x
x 2-inch pan.
Mix condensed milk, sour cream and
lemon
juice.
Spread
evenly
over
the crumb crust. Spoon pie filling
evenly
on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and pecans.

title: baked stuffed grouper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large baking pan, line with aluminum foil (leave foil overlapping to cover fish).
Put stuffing between fillets.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place lemon and lime wedges on top.
Bake approximately 1 hour, checking flakiness.
Roll back foil and garnish with parsley.
Serve directly from pan.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, add the milk, flour, salt and chocolate.
Then add vanilla and nuts.
Blend thoroughly, spread 1/4-inch thick in a shallow greased pan and bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut while warm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs, bananas, flour and soda.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 275° for 1 1/2 hours or until done in center.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Layer dried beef.
Wrap chicken with bacon and place on top of beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: big beef roast
directions: Stir ingredients together and place over roast that has been placed in a big iron skillet or pan and sprinkled with meat tenderizer.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil tightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 3 hours.
Potatoes, carrots, whole cloves and celery can be cooked in the same pan with beef.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 238°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes cool and cut into 1/2 inch cubes, leaving skin on.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cover over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Add potato cubes, salt, pepper, green onions, bacon, cheese and chicken base.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Garnish with additional bacon and cheese.
Can add ham chunks if desired.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onion.
Add soups, noodles and soy sauce.
Mix well and bake in a covered 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Stir halfway between baking time.

title: porcupine meatball
directions: Mix soup with one soup can of water.
Combine rice, ground beef, onion, salt, pepper, and Tbsp of soup, mix well.
Form into balls.
Cook first, then place in casserole dish, cover with remaining soup.
Bake covered at 350 degrees.

title: marble squares
directions: Make brownie mix according to package directions.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Stir the stuffing mix and water in a mixing bowl.
Remove the stems from the mushrooms.
Chop stems.
Cook the mushroom caps in 3 tablespoons of margarine, lightly browning in a skillet.
Remove and place in a shallow baking dish.
In the skillet, stir and cook the mushroom stems and peppers until tender.
Stir into the stuffing in the bowl.
Spoon the stuffing mixture into the mushroom caps.
Drip the tops with the remaining margarine.
Heat under the broiler for five minutes.

title: granola
directions: Because most boxed cereals have preservatives, I began making granola.
Vary the fruits and nuts each time for interesting flavors.

title: cream of lettuce soup
directions: Blend lettuce, bouillon cubes and water in blender until smooth.
In saucepan, melt butter; add onion and cook until tender. Remove onion from pan.
To butter in pan, add cornstarch, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk, keeping smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and boils for 1 minute.
Stir in lettuce mixture.
Add cooked onion and heat to serving temperature. Serves 4 to 6.

title: harvest cake
directions: Important:
Place apples and sugar in bowl; mix well and let set for 1 hour.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour, buttermilk and soda; mix well. Add coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: all-in-one burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Form mixture into patties; layer the patties in foil and refrigerate to firm up.
Broil, grill or bake to desired doneness.
You can also add your favorite seasonings or barbecue sauce.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 loaf pans with vegetable spray. Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
In a separate bowl stir together dry ingredients.
Add dry mixture to batter and mix just until blended.
Stir vanilla, apples and pecans into batter.
Pour batter into prepared loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Mix cheese, milk and chicken together.
Roll out the crescent rolls; flat-tear into 4 sections.
Spoon chicken mixture onto one section.
Fold over to make a turnover.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until rolls brown.

title: fruit-filled jewels(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, cream butter with an electric mixer set at medium speed.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and vanilla, beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add the flour and blend at low speed until thoroughly combined.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until mixed.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk and cocoa together in pan.
Heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Let boil for 2 minutes, then add the peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add seasonings and vegetables.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
To serve, put Frito's in bottom of bowl. Add soup; sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
Add cheese, butter, and garlic salt; stir until cheese and butter are melted. In a measuring cup, beat egg; add milk to measure 1/2 cup.
Stir into grits.
Pour into a greased 1 to 1-1/2 qt baking dish.
Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 10-25 minutes or until bubbly around the edges.
Sprinkle with additional cheese if desired.
Yield: 4-6 servings.

title: strawberry  margarita pie
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and melted margarine.
Spread in a 9-inch pie plate.
Press mixture onto bottom and up sides of pie plate. Refrigerate.
Mix condensed milk, strawberries and lime juice in large bowl until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Pour into crust.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or until pie can be easily cut.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook until tender crisp. Drain and cool.
Chop peppers and onion, then add to cooled carrots.
Mix together tomato soup, vegetable oil, vinegar, salt and sugar; pour over carrots and set for 48 hours.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef with onion, garlic, drain. Add stewed tomatoes and the rest of the ingredients. Cook 1 hour.

title: super mom casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add all but Doritos.
Mix thoroughly and add 3/4 of the Doritos.
Mix again.
Spread into 9 x 13 pan; add remaining Doritos to top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell and have ready.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Add any type flavoring of your choice.
Pour into pie shell.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill to set up.

title: joan's tea cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Work together until smooth.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut cookies.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine; add crushed pretzels. Mix well, then press into 9 x 14-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until smooth; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust.
Chill.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir in strawberries.
Chill until partially set. Spread over cream cheese.
Chill until firm.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: key lime pie
directions: Thoroughly mix gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar, and salt in a saucepan. Beat together egg yolks, lime juice and water;
stir into gelatin mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat just till mixture comes to boiling.
Remove from heat;
stir in grated peel.
Add food coloring sparingly to tint pale green.
Chill, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Beat egg whites till soft peaks form:
gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Fold gelatin mixture into egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pile into cooled pastry shell, chill till firm.
Spread with more whipped cream, edge with grated pistachio nuts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Spray large casserole dish with Pam.
Put mix in dish and sprinkle with topping.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill.
Just before serving, cut a large opening in center of round bread and fill with the dip. Center bread on tray and surround with cubes of bread for dipping. *Fat free or fat reduced works well also.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: After baking, let cake cool, then crumble into a punch bowl or large glass bowl. Top with pineapple and juice. Top that with vanilla pudding. Top that with pie filling. Top that with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: no. 5 salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients and cover (not too tightly). Let stand for 12 hours, more or less, for flavor to blend.
Use as a salad or on top of angel food cake. (I use juices to make jello salad or dessert, or it may be used in punch.)

title: easy cure meat jerky
directions: Mix together the salt, sugar and water for brine and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: red salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a nonreactive bowl and allow to marinate for at least 2 hours before serving.
Taste and adjust seasonings with salt and additional lime juice.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: maryland crab soup
directions: Flour and brown beef cubes in skillet, then add all in large pot and cook on medium heat for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat soup until hot. Add sour cream and chicken.
Mix and keep warm. Soften tortillas in salad oil or dip in hot water. Fill with cheese, sour cream and chicken mixture and onion.
Roll.
Repeat until all tortillas are filled and placed in casserole dish.
Pour leftover mixture over top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin-cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough on a lightly floured surface to a 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Brush surface of dough with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and next 4 ingredients in a small bowl; sprinkle over dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border on all sides. Starting with long side, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Pinch seam to seal (do not seal ends).
Cut roll into 12 slices; place cut side down in a lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Brush with remaining butter.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Remove pan from refrigerator and let rolls rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 50 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake rolls at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and lemon juice; drizzle over warm rolls.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: christmas sugarplums
directions: Mix butter, molasses, raisins and crumbs by hand until well blended.
Pinch off pieces the size of a large olive and wrap each piece around a pecan half.
Roll 30 in sugar, the rest in coconut. Makes 60 sugarplums.

title: cheese puff potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets 20 minutes.
Remove from water and bake until soft.
Split, scrape out carefully and cream with butter, hot milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Replace in shells and cover with grated cheese.
Place in hot oven until cheese melts slightly.
Serve hot.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Marinate chicken pieces about 1 hour.
Barbecue or bake at 400° about 50 minutes.
Baste while cooking.

title: cranberry pear loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 4-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients and mix until just moistened.
Pour into pan and bake 70 to 80 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan, then remove.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer graham crackers (do not crush); cover bottom of pan evenly.
Make sure they are tightly sealed; set aside.
Follow instructions on boxes of pudding, except use 3 cups of milk instead of 4.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread half the mixture over the crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers. Spread other half of pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add a third layer of crackers (create a tight "lid").
Spread chocolate frosting over the top.
Chill for at least 12 hours.

title: wassail punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
(Taste. May need a little longer.)
Remove cinnamon and cloves.
Serve warm in punch cups.
Great for Christmas.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs in a large pot over medium flame, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil. Cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus
directions: Wash and cut off tough ends of asparagus.
Cut spears in about 1-inch pieces.
Boil or steam until tender.
When asparagus is done, make 2 slices of toast.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine and pour over asparagus and toast.
Mix and serve hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with mixer until well blended. Sprinkle in sugar.
Bake in greased and floured pan in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple slices
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix flour, shortening, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and salt like pie crust. Put 1 egg yolk in cup. Add enough milk to make 1/2 cup and add to flour mixture. Roll out half and put on large cookie sheet with sides. Put cornflake crumbs over dough. Put peeled and sliced apples on dough. Put 1 cup sugar and cinnamon over apples. Roll out rest of dough and put over apples. Beat 1 egg white and spread over top crust. Bake 1 hour.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Place flour in large bowl, add dates, chopped orange slices and nuts; stir to coat each piece.
Add flour mixture and coconut to creamed mixture.
Mix with hands.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven 225° to 250° for 2 1/2 hours to 3 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat well.
Mix milk, vanilla and cocoa.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: janice's chicken spaghetti
directions: Make roux with oil and flour.
Add chopped onion, pepper and celery and saute until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, ketchup, barbecue sauce, sugar and Tony's.
Cook 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If sauce becomes too thick; add water as needed.
Add chicken and cook 45 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: quick asparagus casserole
directions: Spread asparagus in a baking dish.
Cover with mushroom soup. Sprinkle crushed potato chips over soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: milk chocolate and peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter and butter, beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla, beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup milk chocolate bits.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate bits and let stand 5 minutes until bits become shiny and soft.
Spread chocolate evenly over top.
Cool.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: confetti pepper relish
directions: Combine red and green peppers, onion and jalapeno pepper in a Dutch oven; add boiling water to cover pepper mixture.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and salt, stirring well. Pour over pepper mixture.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat; boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Chill.
Serve with fish.
Yield:
1 quart.

title: garlic mint dressing
directions: In blender or food processor, blend garlic, lime juice, mustard, mint, sugar and salt until smooth. Add oil slowly and blend until emulsified.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: strawberry champagne sauce
directions: In a blender container, combine strawberries with champagne or for food processor, combine half the ingredients at a time.
Cover and blend or process until smooth.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes 4 cups.
Excellent when served over angel food cake or vanilla ice cream.

title: oatmeal coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir all filling ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and bake 50 to 60 minutes until top and crust are golden and a pick inserted in center comes out clean, but oily (filling may still be jiggly in the center).
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: You will also need a 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Melt jelly; add sauce.
Mix and add sausage.
Put in crock-pot and serve warm.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add salt and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour and knead for 5 minutes.
Form into 15 to 16 balls.
Immediately roll dough balls between hands to form 16 to 18-inch strips.
Do not let the dough raise at any time! Wrap into pretzel form.
Combine egg yolk with 1 teaspoon of water.
Brush onto pretzel top.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: no sugar pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in small electric ice cream freezer or ice cube trays.
If using ice cube trays, partially freeze.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and return to freezer.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 2.

title: beef stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off green peppers; take seeds out and wash in cold water.
Drain.
Brown hamburger with onions.
Add tomatoes, bread crumbs, oregano, salt and pepper.
Mix well and stuff peppers.
Set peppers upright in a casserole dish; pour juice over tops of peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; bake 5 minutes more.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water and finish second cup with pineapple juice.
Place in refrigerator until slightly set.
Add mayonnaise to jello mixture and whip.
Fold in pineapple, pecans and cheese.
Then fold in Dream Whip (prepared to package directions).
Pour into mold or dish and refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake until done. Spread frosting on cake and sprinkle with remaining nuts.

title: chinese venison and vegetables(eat this over hot cooked rice)
directions: Cook venison in the oil until it loses pink color, about 5 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic and celery.
Cook and stir for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook another minute.
Mix 1/2 cup water and soy sauce and add.
Cover and cook about 3 minutes more and add pea pods and tomatoes.
Cook another 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water.
Add and cook until thickened.
May need more water.

title: dorothy's applesauce cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cornstarch; add hot water.
Cook until clear and thickened.
Add vanilla, lemon or both to flavor sauce.

title: eclair pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spoon in one-half of the pudding mixture.
Place a second layer of graham crackers on top and then add the rest of the pudding mixture.
Top with a third layer of graham crackers.
Chill until firm.
Frost with a can of chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla. Beat constantly.
Sift flour, baking powder, and salt; add to first mixture and beat.
Heat milk and butter to boiling point and dump all at once to first mixture.
Bake mixture in sheet pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn; sort out unpopped kernels.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in flavorings and soda.
Pour immediately over popped corn.

title: tangy macaroni salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, white vinegar, Eagle Brand milk and sugar.
Add the cooked rotini, green pepper, carrots and onion.
Stir together and allow to set overnight.
Mixture will thicken.
Stir before serving.

title: greenbrier jello
directions: Chill in a suitable dish.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a large bowl, mixing well. Roll into balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 400°.

title: dream dessert
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch cookie pan (baking).

title: applesauce nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in an ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches) with a fork, scraping corners frequently, until moistened.
Stir batter vigorously with fork for 1 minute. Scrape sides of pan with a rubber spatula.
Spread batter evenly in the pan.
Bake until top springs back, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool. Store loosely covered in refrigerator.

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt together, putting baking powder in last.
Roll in cracker crumbs or flour.
Saute in butter.

title: glazed chicken oriental
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
In 12-inch skillet heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Add carrots and cook about 2 minutes, stirring often.
Add snow peas and scallions; cook and stir 3 more minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender. Use slotted spoon to move vegetables to bowl.
Add remaining tablespoon oil to skillet and heat on medium heat.
Add chicken breast and cook until lightly brown on each side and cooked through.
Move chicken to serving platter and keep warm.
To skillet add garlic and ginger.
Cook and stir over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes.
In small bowl stir water into cornstarch to blend.
Add orange juice and grated peel.
Add to skillet along with soy sauce. Bring to boil stirring; reduce heat.
Cook about 2 more minutes, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Return vegetables and chicken to skillet and cook with sauce until heated.
Spoon rice around vegetables and chicken to serve.
Pour any remaining sauce over chicken.

title: chicken curry casserole
directions: Stew the chicken and pick the meat off the bones.
Mix undiluted soup and mayonnaise until blended; stir in curry powder. Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions, drain and mix together.
Layer vegetables, then chicken, then sauce. Repeat. Top with crumbled potato chips and grated cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove lid and cook an additional 10 minutes to brown top.

title: toll house cookie pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour and both sugars. Blend in cooled butter. Stir in chocolate bits.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour at 325°. Preheat oven.

title: cheese popcorn
directions: Place popcorn into two 13 x 9-inch baking pans.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Combine garlic salt and onion salt; sprinkle over popcorn.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 5 to 10 minutes. Serve immediately.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine sour cream, sugar, flour, salt, almond extract and eggs; beat well.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 30 minutes.
Spread filling over hot pie.
Chill.
Spread whip cream over pie.

title: a better banana bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Combine flour and next three ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Add flour mixture to banana mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan coated with baking spray with flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan on wire rack.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack. Yields 14 servings.
Serving Size:
1 slice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown and crumbly; drain well.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with crescent rolls.
Press seams together.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine rest of ingredients; beat well.
Pour over sausage.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes or until set.
(Can let stand overnight in the refrigerator, then add combined mixture and bake for 25 minutes.) Let set 5 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Wash cranberries and grind.
Peel oranges, saving 1/2 rind of 1 orange.
Grind oranges and 1/2 rind.
Grind apples.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together with 2 1/2 cups of sugar.
Refrigerate 24°, stirring occasionally. Consistency should be thick.
Serve chilled.

title: venison with mushrooms a la moldavia
directions: Marinate the venison in a marinade prepared by cooking onions in white wine, garlic, peppercorns, nutmeg and thyme to taste. When cooled, add the venison and let stand 24 hours.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Cut tips from 5 pounds chicken wings.
Save tips for soup. Put wings in slow cooker.
Combine above ingredients.
Pour over wings. Cover and cook 6 to 8 hours on low.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture gets hotter as it sets. Refrigerate.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together in a baking dish, uncovered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Ready when edges are brown.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with mixer at medium speed until blended.
Mix in next 3 ingredients; then fold in chips.
Drop 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets by tablespoonfuls. Bake at 350° until cookies puff up, then collaspe, about 8 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large casserole dish, place the cooked broccoli in a layer.
Place diced chicken on top.
Next, spread diced onions.

title: yummy bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Spread half of this in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top immediately after removing from oven.
Melt caramels with remaining evaporated milk and drizzle over chips and nuts.
Crumble and put remaining cake mixture on top (may not be crumbly, but just put blobs of it over the entire top and spread with a spoon). Bake another 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown seasoned meat and onions.
Add chili and place in greased baking dish.
Layer meat mixture, then crushed Fritos. Repeat layers.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: creamy enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix yogurt, cottage cheese and onions.

title: cherry fruit chews
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs and stir in Bisquick.
Gently fold in nuts, dates and cherries.
Spread dough in greased oblong pan. Heat oven to 350° and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer potatoes, carrots, celery and water for 20 minutes, then add broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook another 6 minutes.
Melt together Velveeta cheese and chicken soup.
Add to veggies.
Heat; do not boil.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, then add sugar and let cook.
Make jello as directed; chill and add chopped fruits, nuts and sugar when jello is partially jelled.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over meat and soak overnight. Use for kabobs, chuck steak or round steak.
Grill.

title: fruit cake(light)
directions: Mix, leaving fruit uncut.
Cream butter and sugar and eggs. Add flour.
Dredge fruit and nuts.
Bake in greased tube (10-inch) or two (10-inch) pans.
Line pans with greased brown paper.
Baste with brandy or sherry.
Leave out 2 to 3 days before storing. Store in covered container.
Ready in 1 to 2 weeks.

title: angel whip cake
directions: Prepare the devil's food cake.
Cook the marshmallows, orange juice and ginger ale until marshmallows melt.
When cold, whip the heavy cream and add above mixture to cream.
Cover cake with same; leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: This will make enough for 8 chickens.

title: orange sweet potato with red and white kidney beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place potatoes in 1-quart casserole. Top with beans.
Stir together orange juice, olive oil, sage, garlic, salt and cloves.
Pour juice mixture over sweet potatoes and beans.
Place in oven and cook, stirring 2 or 3 times until potatoes are tender, 70 to 90 minutes.
Allow dish to cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp butter
directions: With mixer, blend first seven ingredients.
Chop shrimp and add to mixture.
Refrigerate.
Remove 30 minutes before serving with crackers.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush crackers and save
1/3 cup.
Melt 1 stick oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan; add
crackers; mix and pat into pan.
Mix ice cream, pudding
and milk
and
pour
over
crackers.
Put
in refrigerator, not freezer, until it sets.
Spread with a layer of Cool Whip and
sprinkle
cup
crushed crackers on top. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry jell-o cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Mix Jell-O, pop and hot water together; pierce holes with round toothpick all over cake and pour Jell-O mixture over cake.
Refrigerate until cool.
Mix pudding as directed and add Cool Whip.
Spread over top of cake and refrigerate.

title: low-fat creamy fettuccine
directions: Spray a 2-quart saucepan with nonstick cooking spray; heat until hot.
Cook and stir onion and garlic in saucepan over medium heat until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except fettuccine.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens slightly.

title: maw maw rice's lemon pies(makes 3 pies)
directions: This will make a crust for 1 pie so do this 3 times.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together, except soda.
Add soda to applesauce; mix well.
Add applesauce and jam to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients; mix well and add raisins and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sunny's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in hot water.
Next morning, rinse and cover with hot water and parboil until blowing on a bean, the skin peels or tenderish to squeeze.
I put a dab of butter in to help keep them from foaming over while parboiling.
Last 5 minutes, put in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and finish the parboil.
Drain and rinse well.
In bean pot or large casserole, put half the beans. Cover with water.
Add sugar, dry mustard, molasses, onion and salt pork.
Then add the rest of the beans.
Bake in slow oven, 250° to 300°, for 4 to 5 hours, covered.
Last half hour, uncover to brown.
Stir occasionally during cooking.
Add more water as needed.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and chicken.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: daffodil dessert
directions: Blend flour, margarine and pecans like pie dough.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Chill.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Line pie shell with 1/3 of the sugar and flour mixture.
Cover mixture with 1/2 of the peaches.
Cover with 1/3 of the sugar and flour mixture.
Cover this layer with the rest of the peaches. Top with remaining 1/3 of the flour and sugar mixture.
Cover with whipping cream.
(Do not whip.)
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce oven to 350° and bake for another 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil cocoa, sugar, butter, milk and vanilla together for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal to mixture.

title: pro bowl casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In buttered 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of potatoes, ham, onion and soup sauce.
(Be sure ham is covered to prevent drying.)
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes, or until potatoes are done.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Beat egg and stir in sugar, oil, orange juice and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Then stir in blueberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or in 3 mini loaf pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: red beans and rice(serves six)
directions: Rinse kidney beans twice.
Discard any that look bad.
Put beans in a big, heavy pot, at least 3-quart size (4-quart is better).
Add water, ham and sausage.
Set uncovered on a burner at medium heat.
While the beans are soaking and warming, chop and add scallions, green pepper, celery and onions.
Add thyme and bay leaves.
When the mixture boils, reduce heat and cover.
Stir every 20 to 30 minutes for 3 hours.

title: minty grape cooler
directions: Cook combined sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly and pour over mint leaves.
Add lemon juice.
Cover and steep 1 hour. Strain.
Add grape juice.
Just before serving add chilled ginger ale.
Garnish with mint sprigs and serve over ice.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: red beans and rice with sausage
directions: Cover the beans with water, about 2 inches over the beans and let stand overnight.
When ready to use, drain and reserve the liquid.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix and chill. Roll 1 ball or 2 logs. Roll in nuts and refrigerate.

title: tomato and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, about 7 minutes.
Add tomatoes and salt or sugar; heat and serve.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine in pan, then add orzo and fry until slightly browned, stirring often.
Add rice and saute them together for a few minutes, stirring often. Then add boiling broth and salt, cover and cook on simmer for about 20 minutes.
When water is all absorbed and rice is soft, remove from heat, stir with fork then let rest, covered, for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sausage and new potato kabobs
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 10 to 12 minutes. Meanwhile cut zucchini and kielbasa into 1-inch rounds.
Make mustard glaze:
In a small bowl, combine the oil, mustard and pepper.

title: peppy spread
directions: Mix cheese and cream cheese until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven on baking sheet 50 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar and chocolate chips.
Add milk and peanut butter.
Stir well.
Spoon drop on wax paper and chill.
Store covered in a cool place.

title: barbecue beef stew
directions: Brown beef in oil; add other ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone and cut in small pieces. (Reserve broth.)

Cook rice according to package using chicken broth instead of water. Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in margarine. Combine rice, chicken soup and sauteed vegetables and pour in a casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Line
bottom
of
crock-pot with tortillas.
Add 1/3 of chicken,
tomato
sauce
and soup mixture; sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Repeat
layers.
Cook on high for 3 hours or low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown roast in skillet with oil.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until fork-tender.
Serve with pasta or rice.
Use the sauce as a topping.

title: broiled lamb chops and herbs
directions: Heat broiler.
Rub lamb chops with garlic; brush with olive oil and sprinkle with dried herbs and pepper.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes per side for medium cooked lamb. Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Spread bread lightly with butter.
Remove crusts and cut in cubes.
Place half in buttered casserole.
Cut shrimp coarsely and put over bread.
Add in layers, the olives, cheese and remaining bread cubes.
Beat remaining ingredients together.
Pour over bread in casserole.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Let stand 1 hour. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, until puffed and brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry fluff topping
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook as for seven minutes.
Frosting yields enough for top and sides of three 9-inch layers.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Stem berries; rinse and let dry.

Spread evenly in pie shell. In top of a double boiler, beat egg yolks with sugar and salt. Stir in scalded milk and place over very hot, but not boiling, water until mixture thickens and becomes custard like.
Remove from over hot water and let cool.
Add vanilla; stir and pour mixture over raspberries.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, or until crust is lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: green beans far east
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add water chestnuts and heat through.
Cook onion in oleo until tender.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and sour cream.
Heat through, but do not boil. Drain beans.
Put in serving dish and top with sour cream mix. Serves 6.

title: tex-mix dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Set aside. In a 9-inch pie plate, spread bean dip, then avocado dip, then sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onion, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with grated cheese. Chill. Serve with bite size Tostitos.

title: fruit curry
directions: Use slow cooker "Wear-Ever" Pokey Pot.

title: butter cookies
directions: These cookies are fun for children to make, cut and decorate. They also taste good, especially when frosted with the frosting (recipe below).

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Press some of the mixture around each drained cherry.
Let dry.
Combine chocolate morsels and paraffin in top of double boiler over hot water.
Heat until chocolate and paraffin are melted.
Cool slightly.
Dip balls into chocolate, then place on waxed paper to harden.
Age for 2 weeks.
Yields 75 to 100 pieces.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoons. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a skillet, heat bacon drippings and while stirring constantly, add flour until the mixture becomes a dark brown.
To this, add celery, onion, green pepper, garlic and parsley.
Cook 5 minutes over a medium heat or until tender.

title: manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.

title: italian pizzelle(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add oil, anise seed and vanilla.
Beat well; add flour and baking powder.
Drop a spoonful of batter into the center of the pizzelle iron, close the lid and clip handles together.
Allow to cook about 30 seconds or until steaming stops. Remove with fork.
They cool quickly so if you would like to roll them, do it very quickly.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple crunch cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Stir in brown sugar. Spread pineapple evenly over sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans and oats.

title: cheese delight
directions: Cream together. Dip spears of cauliflower or celery.

title: princeton taffy
directions: Mix together syrup, soda and butter and boil until a small amount dropped in cold water makes a small ball.
Stir in coconut and beat until cool, then roll in balls and place in buttered dish to cool.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar slowly.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamy mixture.
Add orange juice.
Mix well.
Fold in grated orange rind.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: granny's chocolate marvel cake
directions: Into large mixing bowl sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl stir together milk, prunes, vanilla, egg whites or egg substitute and cappuccino or coffee.
Pour moist ingredients into dry ones, blending well. Spray 2 (9-inch) round baking pans with nonstick cooking spray. Divide batter equally between pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until center tests done with wooden pick. Let cakes cool in pans 10 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack and cool. Frost with Party Frosting.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Wipe pieces dry, then saute them until brown in olive oil and margarine.
Salt and pepper while browning.
When well browned, add garlic and onion.
Cook slowly until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes, water and lemon juice.
Cover the skillet and cook slowly for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with rice.

title: cheese biscuits like red lobster
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until it forms a soft dough. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets. Take last 2 ingredients and pour or brush over buns. Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned yeast bread
directions: Put yeast in a cup of warm water with a teaspoon of sugar. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cream together shortening, sugar and salt. Add well beaten eggs.
Knead; let rise and bake.

title: swedish eggs
directions: Peel eggs.
Separate raw egg, slightly beating the white on a small plate and beating the yolk with the milk on another.
Dip each egg in the egg white; coat with sausage and dip in yolk-milk mixture and roll in crumbs.
Deep fry until well browned.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm until all are fried.
Cut in halves, lengthwise and serve hot.
Nice, too, served on toast points with a cheese sauce, as a luncheon dish.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Scald milk with onion over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring constantly. Yields 4 servings.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; combine with brown sugar, pumpkin, dairy half and half, salt and spices.
Cook in top of double boiler over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Meanwhile, soften gelatin in cold water.
Stir into hot mixture.
Chill until partially set. Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add granulated sugar and continue beating until stiff and no longer grainy.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill until set. When ready to serve, garnish with whipped cream or substitute and sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Sprinkle top with brown sugar and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish
and bake for 30 minutes.
This is very rich.	It is best served
with
"table-water" crackers.
Do not use salted crackers. Delicious!

title: punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Heat until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Mix Kool-Aid in 1 quart of water.
Mix all of the ingredients in a gallon jug.
Finish filling the jug with water.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain; add tomatoes (diced), tomato paste and spices.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer, until consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°. Stir together cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Set aside 1 cup of meat and 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese.
In an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, alternate layers of 1/3 noodles, meat sauce and cheese mixture.
Spread reserved meat and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add frozen strawberries, cranberry sauce and undrained pineapple.
Pour half of mixture in a 9 x 13 glass dish or mold and place in refrigerator until almost firm.
Stir sour cream and spread evenly over almost firm gelatin mixture.
Spoon other 1/2 of gelatin mixture over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 3 pieces and boil until tender.
Drain and rinse in hot water and then cold water.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until dinner.

title: coconut fruit cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add
fruit cake mix, dates, coconut and nuts.
Put into flour mixture and mix well. Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and extract.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with orange juice.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in 250° oven.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and add enough water to fill a large punch bowl.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Line pie shell with peach halves. Dot with butter on each peach half. Mix eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla. Cream well and pour over peaches and bake in a moderate oven until done.

title: dad's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until thick and foamy.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Combine mixtures, adding zucchini, pineapple, nuts and raisins. Mix well.
Put in 2 bread pans, greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chile relleno pie
directions: Brown meat with peppers, onions, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper. Seed the chile peppers and spread on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with meat mixture. Sprinkle cheeses on top. Combine eggs, cream and flour; pour on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Pour tomato sauce on top and bake additional 15 minutes. This pie is equally delicious without the beef.

title: lo-fat chocolate cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and milk until thickened.
Beat eggs slightly and add some of the hot mixture.
Continue to add hot mixture a little at a time until all is added.
Continue cooking until thick; add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in top of a double boiler.
Cool. When marshmallow mixture is cooled, fold in Cool Whip.
Mix butter and lemon juice into blueberry pie filling.

title: yum balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate until firm.
Yield: 4 dozen balls.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Do not defrost potatoes.
Mix together.
Drizzle melted margarine or butter over top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Very good next morning with an egg for breakfast.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling water to cover for 10 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Mash eggplant; set aside.
Combine bread and milk; let stand for 10 minutes.
Cook onion and garlic in butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until tender.
Add eggplant, egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: bread pudding deluxe
directions: Butter baking dish.
Add bread, raisins, sugar and salt.
Pour half and half over mixture and let stand 1/2 hour.
Bake at 325° covered for 1/2 hour.
Then remove. Cover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine chicken or turkey and celery in a bowl.
Mix salad dressing, salt, poultry seasoning, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken or turkey and celery.
Toss, cover and chill for 2 hours.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: broccoli-ham ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350. In a bowl, mix ham, broccoli, onion, parsley, mustard, cheese and lemon juice. Arrange crescent triangles in a circle with pointed sides facing out. (5 inch diameter opening in center). Scoop ham mixture onto wide ends of triangles. Bring points of triangles up over filling and tuck under the wider ends of dough at the center. Bake 25-30 minutes until golden brown.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and freeze.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls out flat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage on top.
Layer hash browns, then the 2 cheeses.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, salt, milk and pepper.
Pour mixture on top of pizza.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: asparagus-chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in large casserole dish.
Layer asparagus, egg slices, chicken breasts (chopped), mushrooms, water chestnuts, soup, cheese, stuffing and milk.
Save some stuffing to sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix in 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: veal scaloppine bolognese
directions: Flatten veal with meat
mallet until very thin.
Butter bottom of shallow baking dish,
large
enough to hold the meat in a single layer.
Place Prosciutto and cheese in layers over meat, sprinkling a little
lemon
juice
over each layer.
Dot with butter and season
to
taste
with
pepper
only.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients well (use hand mixer) and pour into buttered baking dish.
Add topping.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Arrange pineapple chunks and bell pepper strips on top of chicken.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue venison
directions: Place venison in big container and cover it with water and vinegar mixture.
Leave in marinade at least 4 hours.
Remove meat and wash it thoroughly with cold water.
Lay bacon strips on top. Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook over low charcoal for 4 hours, basting with barbecue sauce or salad dressing.

title: country chicken 'n biscuits
directions: In greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine first 5 ingredients and 1 cup cheese.
Blend soup and milk.
Pour over first 5 ingredients in casserole.
Bake, covered at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: In a medium bowl, stir first 6 ingredients together.
Stir in next 4 ingredients until blended.
Stir in raisins.
Spray 4 to 4 1/2 cup mold or 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray.
You can:
(A) bake bread 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or (B) after pouring batter into mold or pan, cover tightly with foil. Put mold or pan on a rack in Dutch oven and pour 1-inch of water around pan.
Bring water to a boil and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, adding water as needed.
Remove from Dutch oven and cool on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: pound cake
directions: Eggs, milk and margarine are to be at room temperature. Mix Crisco and margarine well.	Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time. Add
flour with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours
at
Can
make chocolate pound cake by adding 3 tablespoons of cocoa.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Stir and press in pan.
Add sweetened condensed milk, layer of chocolate chips, layer of walnuts and top with coconut. Cook until brown about 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: whipped filling or frosting(freezes well, 3 cups)
directions: Cook flour and milk over medium heat, stirring constantly, until very thick.
Cool.
Cream sugar, oleo, shortening and vanilla until fluffy.
Add to flour mixture and continue beating until consistency of whipped cream.
Should be smooth with no grainy taste.
Can be colored, if desired.

title: spaghetti and pork chops
directions: Saute salt pork, garlic and onion, using a large kettle.
Pour off any excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly 2 to 3 hours, covered.
Prepare spaghetti; drain.
Give each guest a pork chop atop sauce and spaghetti.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand.
Cream shortening or margarine, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to creamed mixture and then add the oatmeal.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: spam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well with mayonnaise.
Serve on crackers or may be spread on bread.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Wash chicken well; dry with paper towels.
In hot butter in large skillet, saute chicken, skin side down, 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute, covered, 5 minutes. Push chicken to one side; add spinach.
Sprinkle with salt and basil.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Turn chicken right side up. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Blend spinach with onion and butter.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: oklahoma dirt pie
directions: Mix ingredients together. Leave some oreos to the side. Pour into cooked pie shell. Chill in refrigerator until firm. Sprinkle remaining oreos on top. Serve and enjoy.

title: baked grits
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients, stirring constantly until it thickens. Add one roll jalapeno cheese and stir until it melts. Add beaten eggs and milk. Mix, then pour in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: out-of-this-world pie
directions: In a saucepan combine the pie filling with sugar and pineapple. Cook until thick and remove from heat.
Add jello.
Allow to cool and add sliced bananas and pecans.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells and top with whipped cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the first 2 ingredients, stirring constantly, until it forms soft ball, then pour over the remaining 2 ingredients.
Stir well and pour into a greased pan.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in an oven bag; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add spaghetti sauce to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Add chicken and green pepper to bag. Turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange chicken in an even layer.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 little slits in top.
Bake until chicken is tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve over hot pasta of your choice.
Serves 5.
Contains 477 calories and 8 grams of fat.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil and stir well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each one.
Add carrots and mix well.
Pour batter into three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lois lochrke recipe for arthritic relief
directions: Empty raisins into a large shallow container.
Pour enough gin (cheapest you can buy) to completely cover raisins; most grocery stores carry both.
Let stand uncovered until all liquid disappears (about 7 days).
Then place raisins in a covered container and eat just 9 raisins a day.
If you don't like raisins, put them on your cereal or in a salad.

title: stir-fry
directions: *Cook on stove top whole in small amount of soy sauce with lid until tender and then chop.

title: hot peppers in tomato sauce
directions: Bring to a simmer, oil, vinegar, sugar, ketchup and salt.
Cut peppers into small pieces, including seeds.
Add peppers to simmering sauce and cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
(If cooked too long, they become soggy.)
Spoon peppers and sauce into pint jars and cold-pack for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Beat eggs; mix in sugar, flour and coconut.
Add milk, melted margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 1/2 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown (about 1 1/4 hours).

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add all liquid ingredients. Stir until mixed well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool and frost with favorite frosting.

title: spicy mexican pie
directions: Cook sausage, onion and garlic in skillet until done.
Drain grease.
Stir in green chilies; set aside. Grease 10-inch pie dish.
Place 2 tortillas on the bottom. Spread 1/2 sausage mixture. Sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese. Add 2 tortillas. Spread with beans. Add 2 tortillas.
Spread with peppers. Add 2 tortillas. Spread with remaining sausage and cheese on top. Cover and bake 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes until hot in center.
Cool 10 minutes. Cut.
Serve with salsa or sour cream.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in an 8-inch square pan. Mix sugar, baking powder, flour and milk well. Then pour over melted butter. Add 1 large can of fruit over dough. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mother's gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, molasses and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water and beat until mixture is smooth.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
