directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk; add 2 beaten eggs and mix well. Add corn; stir well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cut up butter; place all over top of corn casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir corn after 30 minutes.
Continue baking.

title: everybody's favorite cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sugars and shortenings in large bowl with wooden spoon until well blended.
Mix in oats, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in flour, bran, baking powder and soda thoroughly. Stir in peanut butter, candy, nuts and raisins.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool one minute and remove to cooling rack.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; chop in small pieces.
Add green pepper, cucumber, onion and tomatoes.
Mix dressing according to package directions.
Pour over spaghetti; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Beat well before adding.

title: millie mom's chocolate cream pie
directions: Put milk in top of double boiler.
Combine egg yolks, sugar, cocoa and cornstarch together.
Mix a little of the milk in with the dry mixture until it begins to blend, add a little more and stir well.
Then slowly pour the milk into the mixture until well blended before pouring it all back into the top of the double boiler.

title: drop oatmeal surprise cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger biscuit bake
directions: Prepare as for biscuits, or use Bisquick. Mix and roll into two 8-inch squares.

title: reuben croquettes
directions: Cook rice with 1 1/3 cups of water, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and oleo.
Drain kraut as well as possible.
Chop kraut and corned beef very fine.
Add onion, 2 eggs, rice, cheese, 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into 18 balls.
Combine 1 egg and 2 teaspoons of water; beat slightly.
Roll each ball in egg wash and roll in crumbs again.
Cook in hot, shallow oil for 5 to 7 minutes.
Turn once.

title: burnt creme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat cream over low heat until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick and yellow, about 3 minutes.
Beating constantly pour cream in steady stream into egg yolks.
Add vanilla and pour into custard cups.
Place custard cups in baking pan, with 1/2 inch boiling water in bottom of pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove custard cups from water and refrigerate until chilled, about 2 hours.
Sprinkle each custard cup with granulated sugar.
Place on top rack under broiler and cook until sugar topping is medium brown.
Refrigerate before serving.
Serves 6.

title: liver pate
directions: Cut liver in small pieces and saute in butter until done.
Add onions and cook 2 minutes.
Put all ingredients (plus drippings) in blender.
Blend until smooth.
For snappy pate, add 1/4 teaspoon sage and 1/4 teaspoon thyme.

title: cheese sandwich
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Spread on half of English muffin.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Microwave cheese and milk until very soft.
Add onion and salsa and microwave until totally melted, stirring after each minute.
Pour in small crock-pot and serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin parfait
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter and press into bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Combine remaining ingredients.
Fold in 1 quart softened vanilla ice cream.
Pour into crumb lined pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares.
Top with whipped cream and pecans if desired.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into buttered casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter and honey muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine 1/4 cup oats, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Using pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in margarine until crumbly.
Set aside.

title: baked boneless wings
directions: Soak chicken tenders in milk.
Crush crackers and mix with Parmesan, pepper and garlic salt.
Toss tenders with cracker mix and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until brown.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: fruit floats
directions: Mix fruit juice with the lemon juice and ginger ale.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie mix onto small cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool for 30 minutes.

title: beans and ground beef
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper.
Add to other mixture. Put in casserole.
Heat for about 30 minutes at 250°.
This makes a large amount.

title: vivian's chocolate pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and cocoa and blend until smooth.
Add sugar and water.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Add egg yolks and cook until stiff enough to put in cooked pie shell.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat 3 egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until forms stiff peaks.
Top pie and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Break angel food cake in small pieces and add to Cool Whip mixture.
Mix well and put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix sliced strawberries and glaze together and spread over cake mixture.
Refrigerate.
Better if cake sets several hours before eating.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients except rolls.
Using two triangular crescent rolls, shape into rectangle.
Put 1/4 mixture in center. Pinch 4 corners and seal.
Brush with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use either cream of mushroom, celery or chicken soup, slightly diluted with milk, as a gravy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 2 1/2-quart Corning Ware dish.
Sprinkle in raw rice. Cover with chicken pieces that have been salted and peppered. Sprinkle on onion soup mix.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can of water. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Stir in cornbread mix. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Crush crackers; mix with the melted butter.
Pat out in a 9 x 13-inch pan (save 2 cups).
Beat pudding and milk for 2 minutes. Add ice cream; mix well.
Pour over the cracker crumbs.
Put Cool Whip on top, then sprinkle with the remaining cracker crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve.

title: texas tofu
directions: Beat eggs with tamari.
Slice tofu in 1/2-inch thick slices. Dip in egg mixture, then bread with wheat germ.
Flash fry in oil in nonstick pan. Turn once.
Lower heat.
Pour remaining egg mixture over tofu slices.
As soon as it's set, sprinkle cheese over top. Cover and turn off heat.
Warm chili. As soon as cheese is melted, slide entire tofu dish onto platter.
Top with chili. Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, avocado, raw onions, grated cheese and salsa.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Heat soup and cheese. Add mushrooms, water chestnuts and broccoli. Bake at 300. Top with the crumbs.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
(Makes a big batch!)

title: chaiwalla's famous tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
To make biscuit dough, place flour, salt and baking powder in bowl and cut in butter until mixture becomes coarse.
Add enough milk to make dough medium soft.
Place about half of dough onto floured board and roll to fit 9-inch pie pan. Cover dough with tomato slices; sprinkle chives and basil over tomatoes.
Top with half of the cheese and coat with mayonnaise. Add remaining cheese.
Roll remaining dough thinly to fit over top of the pie and pinch cloves.
Bake until brown on top, about 20 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: Wash and clean berries, put on stove with just enough water to cover.
Cook on low heat (add a pinch of salt) until they pop open.
Cool.
Run through colander.
Measure exact amount of sugar and same amount of berries.
Put in cool place and let set until it jells.
Do not cook sugar and berries together, just mix.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake and let cool.
Prepare pudding as directed; fold in cream cheese.
Spread mixture over cooled cake.
Next, spread pineapple and bananas over pudding layer.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine
the first 3 ingredients; stir	into
pineapple liquid in pot over medium heat.
Add vinegar
and	soy
sauce. Bring
to boil, reduce heat and cook	until
thick,
stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add chicken and	the
rest
of the ingredients. Cook for 5 minutes.
Serve on a
bed of rice garnished with the noodles.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fat-free carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; set aside.
Drain pears, reserving juice for another use.
In food processor fitted with chopping blade, process pears until smooth; set aside.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake cookie bars
directions: Beat together cream cheese, egg and sugar until creamy and lump free.
Set it aside.
Then spread 1 roll of cookie dough on the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Spread cheese mixture over dough.
Cover with second roll of dough to cover mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until brown.
Keep refrigerated.

title: larry's luscious peach pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and extract.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: eggs pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar in 1 bowl.
Heat milk and cornstarch, then combine eggs and sugar.
Beat about 5 minutes or until thickening. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done or brown.

title: fried bay scallops
directions: Pour 1/2-inch oil into skillet.
Heat to very hot; drain scallops and pat dry.
Dust scallops with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Check proper temperature of skillet by dropping in one scallop.
If it immediately turns golden brown, the temperature is right.
Add remaining scallops and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, turning to brown on all sides.
Remove scallops with slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Serve immediately. Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.
Excellent with good Muscadet or Chablis Grand Cru.

title: fried apples
directions: Slice apples.
Fry in skillet with Crisco oil.
Salt lightly and the pour a cup of sugar on top.
Cook on medium until candied and mushy (approximately 20 minutes).

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Combine egg, milk, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add ground beef and cooked rice.
Mix thoroughly.

title: peanut blossom
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, and salt, set aside.
Cream together shortening, peanut butter. Add sugar and brown sugar. Mix well. Add egg, milk and vanilla, mix.

Blend in dry ingredients. Shape teaspoon of dough into ball. Roll in sugar and put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 min. Take out, press Hershey's Kiss in middle. Put back in oven for 2 more min.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yield: a lot!

title: crabbies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Split muffins and spread mixture on them.
Cut into quarters.
Place on foil; broil until brown.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook until dough forms ball.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion. Drain. Add next 6 ingredients and transfer to a casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: brown sauce
directions: Heat oil in pan in which meat was cooked.
Mix in flour and cook over low heat until dry and bubbly.
Gradually add stock and simmer until glossy and smooth.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken on one side in hot butter. Turn; cover and cook gently until tender.
In a small saucepan, gently boil together the orange juice, 1 tablespoon honey, soy sauce and garlic until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining tablespoon of honey.
Remove garlic and pour mixture over wings.
Turn them over low heat until glazed.
Makes 2 servings.

title: lentil soup(from the worcester art museum cookbook)
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil; add lentils and simmer for 1 hour.
Add potato.
In a frying pan, saute onion in olive oil.
Add tomatoes and caraway seed and saute mixture for 3 minutes.
Add to soup pot.
Add pickles, lemon juice and more broth, if necessary. Cook until potato is tender, about 1 hour more.
Simmer for about 2 hours total.
Serve with sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, covered. DO NOT ADD SALT.
Mix at least once while cooking.

title: just peachy
directions: Mix all and chill.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower until soft; drain.
Combine all ingredients, except chives, in container of an electric blender; blend until smooth.
Add chives.
Heat well and season to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandmother's sour milk doughnuts
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Combine milk with soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and flour.
Stir into egg mixture and beat well.
If necessary, add more flour to make dough stiff enough to roll.
Roll 1/3-inch thick.
Shape with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep hot fat, 360°, turning once.
Keep fat at uniform temperature.
When doughnuts are brown, drain on absorbent paper.
Makes about 2 dozen doughnuts.

title: smooth creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and milk in a small bowl. Beat with mixer about 5 minutes until blended, then fold in Cool Whip. Frost cake.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook and drain	spinach.
Set aside to cool.
Beat eggs in deep bowl; add
all
other ingredients, one at a time.
Mix well. Spinach goes
in
last.
Bake
at 375° about 40 minutes until slightly brown
and bubbly.
It will "set" after removal from oven.
Does not
puff up like other souffles.
Is more of a one dish casserole
lunch
meal.
Ground ham can be added if desired. Use greased 10 x 10-inch casserole dish.

title: mother's easy egg custard
directions: First heat milk to scalding; add butter.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir into milk.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust which has been brushed lightly with egg whites.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes (may sprinkle lightly with nutmeg before baking if you like nutmeg).
Very easy and very good!

title: cream wafers
directions: This is a very light and delicate cookie; must be handled carefully.
Tedious to make, but well worth it!

title: kahlua cocoa balls
directions: Combine Kahlua, syrup and fruits.
Blend sugar, cocoa, cookie crumbs and pecans.
Combine both mixtures.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: honey glazed baked chicken
directions: Mix together butter and honey. Place chicken in roasting pan with the breast down. Melt the butter and honey. Pour all over the chicken and on the inside. Cut the onion and green pepper in 4 pieces. Place in the pan part of it inside the chicken. Lay the celery inside of the chicken also. Put the bouillon cubes in the pan. Season the chicken to your liking. Add a couple cups of water. Place the chicken, uncovered, for 1/2 hour at 350°, then remove from oven. Turn it over so the breast is up and cover finish baking the chicken for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: pay day bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick margarine and egg.
Crumble and press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients 1 minute on medium speed, blend in butter.
Add flour and cocoa; mix on low speed until well mixed. Put in greased glass dish.
Bake on High 6 to 7 minutes.
Rotate every 2 minutes.

title: cinnamon stars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites.
As they begin to get foamy, gradually beat in sugar.
Continue beating until whites stand in very stiff peaks (should retain the mark of a knife blade).
Set aside 1/2 cup of whites to coat cookies.
Sprinkle whites with cinnamon and almonds and add almond extract.
Stir together gently but thoroughly.
Mixture should be heavy and fairly solid.
Add more almonds if it is too sticky to be rolled out.
Sprinkle pastry board with nuts or sugar and roll out dough to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into star shapes with a cookie cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet and spread a little of the beaten egg whites on each cookie.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cookies should be golden brown and slightly chewy.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into small loaves or 1 large loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour for small loaves and 1 1/2 to 2 hours for large loaf.
Various toppings can be spread onto loaves before baking:
crushed pineapple with a little brown sugar, orange marmalade or nothing.
Serve the meat loaf with tomato sauce.
If baking plain, I add a little water to the roasting pan and bake the meat loaf covered.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in 2-quart dish.
Microwave for 6 minutes.
Stir in vanilla; beat with mixer.
Pour into greased pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: orange cheesecake for microwave
directions: For Crust:
Cook butter, uncovered, on High for 45 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Add crushed graham crackers and 1 tablespoon sugar, mixing well.
Press firmly in the bottom of a pie plate.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, giving pie plate a half turn every 30 seconds.
Set aside.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with foil. Combine first 4 ingredients in shallow dish and mix thoroughly.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and saute about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

Stir in Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Dip chicken in butter mixture and then in bread crumbs, coating well. Arrange in prepared pan. Pour remaining butter mixture over top. Bake until chicken tests done, about 50 to 60 minutes. Serves 4.

title: city "chicken"
directions: You will need one package wooden skewers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Break up bread in a bowl and moisten with hot water.
Beat egg and add seasoning and mix thoroughly.
Add bread mixture to meat and mix.
Add egg mixture and blend well.
Add small amount of milk to mixture to make a smooth consistency.
Pour into loaf pan and shape.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy squash
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together until well blended.
Take the butter and melt in skillet.
Add Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix. Pack into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Reserve some for the top. Put mixture on top of dressing and the reserved dressing on top of that and then dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour in baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip (whipped).
Makes 2 small pies.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add drained pineapple. Mix well, then add lemon juice.
Mix and pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate until well chilled, overnight, if possible.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown meat in oil, remove and cook celery and onions until just tender, remove.
Return meat back to pot and add beef broth; cook until tender.
Blend cornstarch, 1/4 cup broth and soy sauce.
Stir into meat and heat until thick.
Drop chow mein noodles over plate of rice and add chow mein.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar together. Pour the oil over apples and mix with vanilla and then eggs.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese-noodle-spinach casserole
directions: *I always use 1 bag fresh spinach and steam for a couple of minutes.

title: cobbler (any fruit)
directions: Melt butter; mix sugar, cake flour and baking powder.
Spread evenly in buttered baking pan; add fruit with water or juice and 1 cup milk (sweet or buttermilk).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar thoroughly; then add one egg at a
time.
Then add sifted flour with a pinch of salt, a third at a time.
Continue beating on low for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Then
on
low
add 7-Up, a third at a time until mixed well.
Increase
speed
to	higher for 3 minutes, then reduce to low speed for 1 minute.
Pour batter into Bundt pan sprayed
with Pam.
Bake	at
350° for 1 hour.
Test with cake tester;
if it comes out clean, cool for 7 minutes.
Then turn cake
out
on
a cake disk.	Leave uncovered until cool. Then put cake on dish.

title: vegetable medley dip
directions: Chop vegetables fine; season with celery salt, pepper and seasoned salt to taste.
Mix gelatine and hot water in a separate bowl.
Add mayonnaise.
Fold this mixture into vegetables. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook beans until they are about 1/2 done.
Cook hamburger. Drain.
Add beans.
Put remaining ingredients in the beans and meat.
Cook until beans and vegetables are done.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Drain pineapple.
Save the syrup.
Arrange pineapple in the sugar mixture.

If desired, also arrange maraschino cherry halves, rounded side down, in the sugar mixture. Add enough water to pineapple syrup to make 1 1/3 cups liquid. Add this and 2 eggs to the cake mix and mix as directed on the label.
Pour batter over fruit.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, oranges and celery.
Dissolve jello in hot water and cool.
Add sugar, nuts, celery, berries and oranges. Chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix (dry). Don't mix.
Sprinkle nuts evenly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Great with ice cream.
Very easy.

title: veg dip
directions: Serve with vegetable tray.

title: quick chicken and dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread mix as directed and cook.
Remove from oven and allow to cool 5 minutes. In a large bowl, combine crumbled cornbread, onion, poultry seasoning, celery soup, chicken soup and canned chicken.
Mix thoroughly.
Add water, if needed, to get desired consistency. Turn into large baking pan that is slightly greased. Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes or until browned. Serves 6 to 8.

title: santa's punch
directions: Get out your favorite cookie recipe.
Use this recipe for the cookie dough, but reduce the amount of flour by 1/2 cup.
Cover the mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: louisiana chicken dish
directions: Cook onion and chilies in small amount of shortening until onion is tender.
Add soups to broth; add this mixture to onion mixture.
Layer cooked chicken, chips and broth mixture in baking dish until all is used.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until the cheese is melted.

title: barbecue
directions: Mix all together.
Brush on chicken or pork chops on the grill as you turn.

title: basic meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Form into about 18 meat balls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Arrange in dish and cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave, covered, on Full power for 5 to 7 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.
Drain.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres mold
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin in water and add.
Cool slightly. Add all other ingredients.
Put in mold.
Chill at least overnight.
Decorate with green olive slices.
Spread on crackers with small knife.

title: holiday delights(chewy raisin walnut shortbread bars)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. Combine flour and sugar.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture resembles fine meal.
Press into greased pan. Bake for 20 minutes or just until edges are lightly golden. Meanwhile, combine eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in baking soda, walnuts, raisins and coconut.
Spoon over hot crust; spread to cover evenly.
Return to oven; bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until top is set.
Cool completely; cut into bars.
Yields 20.

title: skillet barbecued chicken
directions: Heat shortening in heavy skillet; add chicken and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add onions, green pepper and garlic to pan.
Saute 5 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients and simmer until thoroughly blended.
Return chicken to skillet. Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: dutch baby pancake
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Then beat in flour, a little at a time, then milk.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.

title: strawberry tunnel cake
directions: Invert cake onto serving plate.
Cut 1/2-inch slice crosswise from top of cake; set aside.
With sharp knife, cut around cake 1 inch from center hole and 1 inch from outer edge, leaving cake wall 1 inch thick.
Remove cake from center, leaving 1-inch thick base on bottom of cake.
Reserve cake pieces.

title: coffee date nut loaf
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Combine coffee soda, egg and shortening; add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to dampen dry ingredients.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: taco roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread a thin layer on each taco shell.
Roll up shell like a hot dog; refrigerate.
(Best if left in refrigerator overnight.)
When firm, slice into 1/2-inch or smaller pieces and serve.
This makes an excellent hors d'oeuvre!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cranberries, pineapple with juice and wine or cranberry juice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Refrigerate to set.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is well blended.
Divide mixture into 4 or 5 portions and add different food coloring to each, plus a pinch of dish detergent which will facilitate clean-up.
Use when cool.

title: spinach artichoke casserole
directions: Drain hearts and chestnuts - reserve liquid.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Mix in melted butter, sour cream, chestnuts, and hearts.
Add spinach and about 1 c. of crumbs.
Mix in enough liquid to make moist*, almost soupy.
Top with parmesan cheese then buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees until hot, about 15 minutes.

title: potato candy(kids recipe)
directions: Combine potato, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time. Mixture will liquify at first, then thicken.
When mixture reaches a thick dough consistency, knead it.
All the sugar may or may not be used.
Cover with a damp cloth and chill.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls and dip into chocolate.
You may use dipping chocolate or combine 12 ounces of chocolate chips with 2 squares of melted unsweetened chocolate and 1/2 cake of melted paraffin, melted in double boiler.

title: party punch
directions: Pour Hawaiian Punch and ginger ale in punch bowl.
Keep sherbet frozen; put in punch last.
Slice orange up.
Put in punch to garnish.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Arrange in 8-inch square pan.
In small saucepan melt oleo; blend in flour and salt.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk; heat until boiling and thickened, stirring occasionally.
Blend in cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.
Garnish with tomato slices.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: pan pizza
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add water, spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Stir together and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into a 9 x 13 inch pan and top with cheese, onion, green pepper, olives and pepperoni.
Keep hot in a 400° oven.
Mix together the eggs, milk, oil and flour until smooth.
Pour over the meat mixture.
Bake
for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder; set aside. Blend together Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add rolled oats, vanilla and chips.
Roll dough into balls and place on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti or lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger.
Mix spaghetti sauce with hamburger.
Mix cottage cheese with eggs.
Layer of noodles.
Layer of sauce.
Layer of cottage cheese.
Layer of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat the above and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: creamy corn bread salad
directions: Prepare and bake corn bread, using

package directions. Cool; crumble into large bowl. Add green onions, green pepper, tomatoes and ham; toss well. Blend cream cheese, salad dressing, cucumber salad dressing, salt and mustard in small bowl. Pour over corn bread mixture; mix well.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer, then add pie filling. Place in graham cracker crust and chill 3 or 4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Spoon one-half of the batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Combine spices and raisins; stir into remaining batter.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool completely.
Spread coconut filling between layers.
Spread top and sides with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle cake with chopped pecans.

title: spicy-seasoning mix
directions: Combine chili powder, coriander, cumin, salt, oregano and red pepper.
Store, covered, in airtight container.
Before using, mix to blend.
Yield:
About 1/4 cup.

title: bob's cucumber salad
directions: You will need three pint jars and lids.

title: ice cream cake roll
directions: Beat eggs; put in sugar slowly.
Add hot water and vanilla. Mix together cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Wet towel and sprinkle 10x sugar on it.
Roll cake up and let cool off.
When cool, fill with ice cream.
Roll up again and put in freezer.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine.
Add flour and cook until smooth.
Add cream slowly, then cheese and seasoning. Simmer until cheese melts.
Cook green beans in salt water.
Drain and mix with sauce.
Add water chestnuts and top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead; refrigerate.
Then bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg
and
allspice.
Mix
in
remaining ingredients. Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix sliced cukes, onions and salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Mix vinegar and sugar.
Pour over cukes and onions.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into plastic containers and freeze.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower and soup. May need to add small amount of water. Pour into 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with French fried onions. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up 4 slices of bread.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown and drain 1 pound sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over sausage.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese, sausage and bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Other meats can be used (bacon, ham and hamburg).

title: banana bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs and bananas.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to banana mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add mustard, sugar and flour; stir real good. Then add water, vinegar and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until comes to a boil and thickens.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except last two.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 10.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook 6 servings of Minute rice. Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: easy beef roast
directions: Wash and dry ham thoroughly or wipe well with a warm cloth. Put ham in large brown bag (grocery bag is fine). Twist end of bag together and secure with garbage bag tie. Place in large pan. Cook in preheated 300° to 350° oven. It will take ham at least 1 1/2 hours to heat through (allow 30 minutes for each pound of heating). When ham has cooked, remove from oven. Be very careful when opening bag; it will be full of steam. Carefully remove ham from bag. Place in a large clean pan. Pour 1 cup pineapple juice with brown sugar or 1 cup Coca-Cola over top of ham. Return to oven for 15 additional minutes. This ham falls off the bone. It is delicious.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Roll into balls or shape into fingers. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from the pan and cool slightly.
Roll each cookie in confectioners sugar.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and mix well. Slowly bring to a boil. Cook until soft ball stage is reached.
Remove from heat. Add the peanut butter and vanilla. Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until creamy and gloss is lost.
Spread in buttered pan. Cool and cut.

title: hot tuna and cheese buns
directions: Mix together and fill 12 sandwich buns with mixture.
Wrap sandwiches in foil and heat in 250° oven for 30 minutes.
For smaller servings, cut in 4 pieces.

title: macaroni goulash
directions: Cook macaroni 8 minutes; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain all fat from hamburger.
Add salt and chili powder.
Mix in macaroni, then add cheese.
Mix and serve.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix the sugar, oil, vinegar, vanilla and cold water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: white trash(snack)
directions: Pour cereal into a large bowl. Set aside. In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Mix and stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla. Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large plastic bag or brown bag with powdered sugar.
Shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 10 cups.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: In a microwave-safe, 2-quart casserole, cook meat on High for 5 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Drain off fat; place meat in a bowl.
Add taco seasoning mix; stir until combined.

title: raisin zucchini bread
directions: Finely shred zucchini to measure 2 cups; set aside.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder; mix well. Add raisins and nuts to dry ingredients.
Combine with zucchini mixture; mix well.

title: soap crayons
directions: Fill measuring cup with water to the 1/8 mark.
Add soap flakes to the measuring cup until the 1 cup mark is reached.
Stir the mixture until it is a thick paste with no lumps.
Then mix in several drops of food coloring.
Press spoonfuls of the mixture into the ice cube tray.
Set it in a warm dry place for a few days until the mixture has hardened.
Pop out and you are ready to color.

title: hearty chicken bake(this recipe aims to please!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine mashed potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions; mix thoroughly.
Spoon potato mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread potatoes across bottom and up sides to form shell.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
It is better to mix the night before using.
Can be used as a salad or dessert.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Fry onion in shortening until lightly brown.
Add tomatoes; bring to boil.
Add corn meal slowly and cook and stir 10 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced iced tea
directions: In a large kettle, bring the first 4 ingredients to boil. Remove from heat and add tea bags. Cover and steep for 5 minutes. Remove and discard tea bags, cinnamon and cloves. Stir in sugar and juice concentrates. Chill and serve over ice.

title: honey lime pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops; place in a shallow baking dish.
Combine lime juice and next 3 ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Coat large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot. Add chops, reserving marinade.
Brown meat 3 to 4 minutes each side.
Add marinade, cover and cook 5 minutes, until done as desired.
Serves 6.

title: apple pizza
directions: Combine flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
In saucepan, heat water, milk and butter to 120° to 130°.
Add to flour mixture, then add egg.
Gradually stir in more flour to make a soft dough. Cover and let rise 1/2 hour.
Roll dough out on 12-inch pizza pan, then cover with cream cheese and sugar.
Top with apple filling and bake at 350° until edge is golden brown.
This is also delicious with cherry or raspberry filling!

title: cinnamon crisp
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until well blended.
Add molasses, vanilla and eggs to creamed mixture; blend well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet (a big tablespoonful).
Press each cookie flat with fork.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: honey buttered pecans
directions: Heat honey and butter in small saucepan until butter is melted and mixture is smooth.
Gradually pour over popcorn and nuts.
Mix until thoroughly combined.
Spread mixture on 2 ungreased jelly roll pans (15 x 10 x 1-inches).
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, turning 2 or 3 times, until golden.
Cool in pan on wire racks. Break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: *May include oregano, garlic, pepper, salt, onion powder, etc.

title: bread pudding muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except raisins and cubed bread.
Mix well.
Add raisins and bread. Mix well and allow to soak 5 minutes.
Spray standard size muffin tin or custard cups with nonstick vegetable coating.
Mound mixture into each of 10 to 12 cups and bake about 35 minutes or until firm. Cool on rack at least 10 minutes before removing from cups.

title: shahi tukray(bread pudding)
directions: Toast bread slices until golden brown.
Next, heat shortening on medium-high heat.
Place bread slices in oil one at a time until reddish brown (about 10 seconds each side).
After you fry the bread pieces, lay them down in a pan in a single layer or layer the slices.

title: tomato refresher
directions: Mix all ingredients except ice.
Serve over ice.
Garnish each serving with celery stick if desired.
Makes 6 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, Karo syrup, maple syrup, margarine, salt, chopped pecans and vanilla. Spoon into 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Arrange pecan halves on top. Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: rose's shoyu sauce(teriyaki sauce)
directions: Bring all ingredients to a near boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: two step chicken broccoli divan
directions: In shallow casserole arrange broccoli; top with chicken or turkey.
Combine
soup
and
milk; pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter or oleo with dry bread crumbs and sprinkle over
cheese.
Bake
in conventional oven at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: vichyssoise soup
directions: In a 3 to 4-quart pot, warm butter over medium-low heat and saute leeks until wilted, approximately 5 minutes.
